We ла read the names and then each group went its own way to a seminar ла room.  I wondered how I would cope with the new situation and if ла I would succeed as a group leader.

She sounded as if she had been waiting for the ла death of my grandmother.  I had lost a person close to me.  I ла felt guilty too as I had been bad to my grandmother of late.  I had not ла remained calm when she no longer understood everything so well.

I did not quite mean what I said and I felt ла ashamed at having been mean enough to criticize him as he is also ла a friend of mine.

I had told my boyfriend that I did not want to go on with our ла relationship.  I knew that I was important to him but I wanted to ла be free.  I saw that this was difficult for him but I remained ла firm and did not change my mind.

[ A successful lesson.]

In the dark an unreal figure formed by a shadow.
[ When I was treated unfairly, regardless of my motives or deeds.]

On a social occasion, I noticed that I reacted on the basis of my ла autonomous nerve system (I could not help it).
When I caused needless anxiety to a person close to me because of ла my lack of self-insight.
I was coming home from an exam and I supposed that I had ла passed it so I ran to a restaurant for a beer.
I had been drinking with a pal and I later (1 o' clock) had a date  ла with my fiancee.  We were going to a Spanish lesson and I was ла afraid that she would smell that I had been drinking.

My fiancee and I were at my parent's place watching TV. There ла were  only two TV-chairs and we were sitting on them when my ла drunken brother came in and rudely chased my fiancee off the ла chair she was sitting on.
I had drunk a couple of beers and my fiancee got angry at me.
We were at a hamburger bar and a man at a table nearby started ла coughing and spitting into his plate.
We got into a fight with some chaps in front of our family house. ла The value of the property destroyed was approximately 15 000 FIM. ла I felt ashamed when my parents came to know about this.

We had had a party the night before and we still had some liquors ла left the morning after. I went to the kitchen pretending to ла prepare some tea and was caught by my fiancee pouring some rum ла down my throat.
While dancing in a restaurant last week.

I was on the Inter Rail in Naples alone. After an evening in a ла restaurant I was going back to the hotel when a prostitute ла approached me to sell herself. I refused but as I carried on ла walking I felt that I was being followed by someone.

I was on my way back from the Inter Rail, on board the ferry from ла Stockholm when my father called me at 7 o'clock to tell me that my ла uncle had died and that I would be seeing him off on his final ла journey within four days.

The death of my grandmother.

My father had a heart attack when I was not at home (I was still ла living with them).  He recovered relatively well although he had ла to retire (which implied relief from the stress of a small scale ла enterprise).
At my grandmother's detestable and selfish conduct towards my ла elder sister, although her behavior was due to senility and lack of ла understanding.

On the cliff by the sea, the silence and the sudden voice of a ла bird.(swans of the bay)
A dark night when I had to go to the outdoor lavatory.

The long lasting illness of my grand-mother, and the changes in ла family relationships caused by it.

A truth expressed unthinkingly at a coffee party.  I realized ла later that I had been inconsiderate, at a wrong moment and the ла wrong place.

While watching TV (a war movie), I felt a strong fear of death, ла threat and fear of loosing people close to me.
I was angry with a friend of mine who behaved in an affected ла manner.

I made a long-distance call to people rather close to me and I ла thought about the sad incident that had happened to them in the ла near past; I knew that they were thinking about it too when I made ла the call.

When my friend let my personal matters be publicaly known.
When I think about my family (parents, brothers, sisters) guilt ла is a part of my feelings.

When my father was very drunk and raging at home.
When I did not find the rack used for beating up rugs, in the ла yard.
When one of my cat died of a disease.
I felt disgusted at the environment while getting back to my ла student lodging. I did not see anything in the suburb which had ла been planned by taking people's comfort into account.
My girlfriend was away visiting another city and I brought ла another girl home. Next morning when I started getting sober I ла felt quite ashamed of myself.
I got 100 FIM too much when I changed money at the bank.  They ла soon called me at my job and the situation was embarrasing for ла me.

In Sweden, a friend and I lived in an appartment owned by a Finn. ла  One day, this man came back to the appartment heavily drunk ла (hashish and alcohol).  He was quite dizzy and he broke down, and ла I could not foretell his reactions.  However, nothing happened.
I had an appointment downtown, and the person in question was ла half an hour late.
The death of my grandmother.
In the army, I had been in hospital for two weeks and as soon as ла I returned to the company, a sergeant ordered me to fetch a load ла on the tractor trailer.

On the way back from a Summer spent in Sweden, I drunk with a man ла in the train.  I had drunk so much that when I got home I fell ла asleep in the entrance hall.  I have never drunk that much, ла neither before nor after that incident.  I was ashamed because my ла mother and my sister had to see me in that state and my father ла had to carry me to bed.
While at primary school, I did not let a friend ring a bell ла although he would have liked to do it.  Afterwards I felt bad.
I got a fairly large amount of my taxes back.
I was jogging in the forest, in the central park area, when I saw ла a man hiding behind a tree.  I got frigthened, turned around and ла ran out of the forest.

I was coming home in a taxi with a fellow worker of mine.  He was ла criticizing my earlier conduct towards him, which to my mind was ла unfounded.  When I reached home, I ran out of the taxi and ла slammed the door.
I had had a farewell party at the place where I had been working ла for a year.  That night I could not fall off to sleep.  I was sad ла thinking that I would not see my nice fellow workers again.
I was travelling in a local train when a drunkard, smelling ла terribly, entered the same carriage and started eating fish that ла was stinking.
While quarelling with a fellow worker of mine, I was vehement and ла irritated and I told him what I thought of him in plain language.  ла I was ashamed of myself when I met him the next day.
I was working as a secretary.  My boss was to go to give a ла lecture, and wanted me to give him the exact address of the ла place.
A sunny Autumn day, after a long rainy period.
Years ago, on my way to school by the forest path I came across ла an exhibitionist.
A person close to me mistook my good intentions for bad, and ла therefore associated unpleasant traits to me.
[ A person close to me told me that his positive regard depended ла on my conduct.]
When an untidy and heavyly drunk person made endeavours to ла approach me.
As a little girl, I was sick in the middle of a school day and I ла vomitted in the basin of the classroom.
I lost my self-control and raised my voice at a child.
I got to know that I had been accepted at university.
I had been watching a TV-program on paranormal phenomena.  At ла night I could not fall off to sleep as I feared that humanoids ла were on the move.
My superior blamed me for some neglects at work in front of ла others.  In fact, the task in question was not supposed to be ла done by me.
My father suddenly fell ill and died.
When a friend of mine got drunk and started to blame and scorn my ла other friends and me.
When I forgot a promise made to a friend of mine.
It was my turn to cook dinner.  I forgot a dish (the favourite of ла the family) in the oven and it got burnt and was uneatable.
My joy was the joy of meeting again.  My husband came home after ла having been away for weeks (for work).  I was on the railway ла station to meet him.

column41: The death of my father made me feel quite guilty, because my ла attitude towards him had been cold and indifferent.
My mother, sister and I were thinking about old times, our ла childhood, and we had a very happy time.
My husband had gone to drive a strange, broken car.  At the ла agreed time, he had not returned, and I feared that he had had an ла accident.

A young, close relative of mine died, leaving behind a baby a few ла months old.

A series about Freud was shown on TV.  In it, a tampon had been ла set in the nose of a woman, and forgotten there.  After great ла pain it was taken off (close-up picture), the woman was bleeding ла from the nose and the mouth.

A borrowed car broke down while I was using it.  It was not my ла fault, nevertheless I felt guilty.
I started a new branch of studies after having failed a former ла one.  When I got back my exam papers I was very happy to know ла that I almost had full marks.
I was diving below the ice, in a cave, at a depth of 26 metres.  ла Visibility was almost zero and the oxygen level decreased ла threateningly.  There were three of us divers on one safety rope.
My mother carried on using mental pressure concerning something ла which was serious and a real burden to me.
My grandfather died, I went to the mortuary and saw the corpse.
[ The same as in anger.]
As a child when I was blamed for peeing in the swimming-pool.

A friend of mine was drunk and having an argument on the street ла with a woman, appparently his girlfriend.  I was walking on the ла other side of the street and thought that I was not supposed to ла interfere.  Later I heard that he had shot himself that evening.

Watching a violent movie.

column41: My grandmother was about to die, and it had the effect that at ла night, after having read a book, and once in bed, in perfect ла darkness, the fear arose that I too may suddenly die.
When I checked my examination paper and realized that I had been ла careless, thoughtless, lazy and hasty so as to make unnecessary ла mistakes concerning things I know and understand.
When we decided, my boyfriend and I, that we would separate, I ла realized that he would have wanted to continue our relationship ла and the coming separation hurt him.

When an acquaintance of mine told me about the way his parents ла treated their sons in an unequal manner.  The most successful of ла them got continuous encouragement, and the youngest was not ла encouraged and was rejected.

I was talking to a friend of mine about our parents and ла education.  I said something and then realized that I did not ла know my friend's parents, their motives and education.  I felt ла ashamed at having talked about something I did not know anything ла about.
My mother told me that the enveloppes that I had been tearing (I ла had torn the stamps away) in good faith had been the first-day ла enveloppes which my father had collected as a young man.

I am not especially good at English, and after the high school ла graduation exam in English I tensely waited for the result the ла whole day.  In the evening, when I heard that I had done ла excellently, I became very happy and the anxiety vanished.  My ла family was at home.

I feared that I was pregnant.  It was not planned and I would ла have been compelled to have an abortion, which I would not have ла liked at all.  Fortunately, after a week's anxiety, I got to know ла that I was not pregnant.
A member of a religious sect tried to convert me, using really ла evil tricks to persuade me.  After he had left, I was anxious and ла angry for a long time. After the event, I was alone.
When my boyfriend wanted to leave me, I felt sad and melancholic.
In a film, there was an episode where they used a chain saw to ла cut a man.  I could not look at it, but I could not avoid ла listening either.  I sought shelter in my boyfriend's arms.

I thought I would be able to use the mangle of the house, and so ла I did not want any help.  However, I blocked it and I had to get ла the janitor to help me out.  He reproached me for not having ла followed the instructions

I promised my friends that I would take care of something, but I ла kept forgetting about it.  When they asked me about it, I ла promised to do it immediately.  However, I got started only after ла a couple of months.  I felt that I had betrayed my friends.
When I got an unexpected letter from  a guy, who had been my school ла mate.
When my brother went to shoot wild ducks, I feared that the ла boat would overturn and he would drown or that the gun would ла accidentally go off.

My father had once again told me that I should be careful and try to ла seek admission to other places also apart from the faculty of ла Social Sciences at the university of Helsinki.  I was not at all ла interested in any other place and had no time to study for other ла entrance exams.
I would have liked to go out to chat with some acquaintances, but ла I realized that I was not wanted.  I felt hurt, disappointed, ла lonely and deserted.
When an acquaintance (he was drunk) of my room-mate vomitted on the kitchen ла carpet.  It was past mid-night and my room-mate had just moved in, ла this acquaintance had helped her move in.ла
I was carried away while talking about my visits abroad and I ла tended to boast a little, till I realized that the listener was ла amused.
When I was baby-sitting at my cousin's place, I tried to have a ла pleasant time and did not really take care of the child.  I do ла not care very much about children.
When I got 21/30 points in an exam of statistics. The result was ла unexpected and it made me realize that statistics do not ла surpass my abilities, as I have sometimes thought.
When a big angry dog put its snout on my arm and had I made one ла movement it would have bitten me.
When my room-mates were watching video-tapes and prevented me ла from watching the news.  The first feeling I had was that I was ла being treated unfairly and then came the feeling of anger.
[ When after a night of sleeping in another's arms, one wakes ла alone and knows that the lonely arms of the night are not the ла same that one meets in the morning.]
When an unpleasant person tried to make friends with me.  A ла subtle, small, insignificant, grey being whose helplessness and ла neutrality evoked the feeling of disgust in me.
Badly chosen words to a vague acquaintance of mine made me feel ла ashamed at having given the wrong impression about what I wanted ла to say.  Thoughtlessness.
When I behaved improperly - fought in a public place.  ла Afterwards, I felt guilty about my conduct.
When my friend told me that he would come and meet me in a ла moment.
My father had been drinking and I feared him when we went to bed ла at night.
My friends promised me that they would definitely call me to tell ла me if they were visiting me or not.
A close friend of mine had not contacted me for a long time.
A friend of mine came to see me when he was quite drunk.
I said something especially stupid which I did not mean at all.
I did not go to help a friend of mine, though she probably needed ла me.
When I felt that an exam, which I had feared, was an easy one and ла went well.
I was afraid when my dog ran out through a crack in the fence ла when  a train was coming.

When a friend of mine was drawn into a fight because of the ла stupid gang he belonged to. I felt angry with him and his ла friends. They could not think about anything sensible, but would ла fool around without taking into consideration the feelings of ла other persons.ла
I felt sad after having had an argument with my boyfriend.  I felt ла that he did not understand me and that there was no point in ла carrying on with the relationship.
I detested my father who was a drunkard.  He would rave, ла threaten and blame my mother and me.  He finally drove us away ла from home.
When I was on holiday with my former boyfriend, he hit me and ла behaved in a very evil and ugly manner in front of the hotel ла personnel.
When as a child I stole, from a friend of mine, the ring she had ла got in an easter egg.
When I got home from a pleasant trip abroad, I got to know that I ла had been accepted at university.
At school, I had acted against the will of the group, and the ла next day they promised to take revenge on me.

My mother had for some time been trying to separate me from a ла good friend who, she thought, was not good company for me.  ла Finally, at breakfast one day, we had an argument and I tried to ла defend my friend.
I got to know about the death of a close friend.
When I was watching a movie with many violent episodes.  They ла accurately showed the cutting of corpses, etc...

When I was caught telling a white lie.  At that time, I was not ла allowed to stay outdoors after 8 p.m.  One day when I was late, I ла made up a story that our neighbour had invited me to his place, ла though I had actually forgotten about the time while playing with ла my pals.
When before the last exam I have taken, I went out instead of ла studying.
When I was pressing figures on the curtain cloth. I had bought ла the cloth after months of hindrances.

I am a kindergarten teacher and I am thoroughly weary of my job.  ла After having taken the university entrance exam I suffered from ла anxiety for weeks as I did not want to carry on with my work - studies ла were the only alternative.
My life-partner, who was drinking more and more, spoke about ла kicking the cat.  He had never done anything of the kind, but I ла knew that he would do so one day, without thinking about it.
Estrangement from my best woman friend.  We have been going ла different ways for quite some time now, but the break was total ла when she got married as her husband is unreasonably jealous of me.

My life-partner is going through a crisis (way of life, old-fashioned values) ла and can only get out of it by talking bold decisions.  I have ла noticed his cowardice and attempts to escape his problems by ла drinking.  I detest his drinking and his being full of self-pity.

Again, a quarrel had come up in our difficult relationship.  My ла life-partner threw all the books off the shelf.  I am sure that it ла disturbed our neighbours since this happened late in the night.

A lonely, neurotic, shy girl lives nearby. She has expressed a ла wish to meet me, I have however avoided her (turned down an ла invitation) as the crisis my partner is going through uses up all ла my empathy.
Begining the week-end with my girlfriend : cozyness, beer and ла wine.
The fear about my future : work, making ends meet and health. ла Coping.
A friend of mine ridiculed me, telling me that I would never ла accomplish anything. I felt that he had interfered with my life.
I felt sad at having to leave my girlfriend after constant problems ла and failed attempts at reconciliation.  My sadness was caused by ла the irreversibility of the decision.
A man spat on the wall of a house.
In an express bus I sat on a seat meant for senior citizens and ла invalids.
When I did not succeed in finding a job after having finished a ла nonacademic degree.
When after an overwhelming anxiety and enquiry, I understood ла something about why I exist and what my task in life is.
At the railway station, while waiting for the last train at night ла I noticed that a drunk young man was appraching me in a ла purposeful mannner.

When I think that I will probably never have a genuine contact ла with my parents.
While reading Olli Jalonen's new book, the distant, cold and ла selfish relationships between people (in the book) made me feel ла disgusted.

When I noticed that my little sister was sulking, because I could ла not meet her because of a misunderstanding.

The day I got to know that I would get a shared dwelling with my ла boyfriend.  My parents place was getting a little crowded with ла my growing bother wanting a room to himself.  I first felt doubt, ла then joy, but also sadness.  The feeling of joy was the ла strongest.
My grandfather had lung-cancer and was being nursed at ла home.  I felt fear when I was alone with him and he almost choked ла on mucus secretions.
The outrageous conduct of a relative towards me and those close ла to me.(blaming us and lying)
We had to finish the life of our 8 year-old dog.
A very drunk person.
An argument that grew out of an ordinary conversation with a ла person very close to me, when we should have been having a good ла time together.
While trying to get my little brother over a ditch, he fell on ла his head and started crying.  I was scared of having caused him ла permanent injury.
[ A chat on the telephone with a friend.]
[ Meeting some new (unpleasant) people or some new, demanding ла situation.]
[ For example, unfair pushing in a bus.]
[ When I am, in my opinion, not understood correctly. ]
[ When some people act very important in any situation.]
[ Generally, when I am late in attending to matters (for example ла paying bills).]

column41: I was travelling back home by boat with two friends of mine after ла a lovely holiday trip.  The night and the sea were dark, and the ла wind was blowing.  I feared that death was there on the boat, I ла somehow felt sure about it.  I feared being left alone.

I was at home, filling my tax report.  Nobody had time to help ла me.  I would have liked to do it quickly so that I could go and ла meet a friend of mine who had just returned from hospital.  I got ла angry as both my brother and my father refused to give me their calculator ла as I had not asked for it nicely.  I could not leave as I ла had to wait for help and the tax report had to be done.

I tried to talk to my parents over the phone, as I wanted to go ла home for the week-end and I knew that I would not be able to bear ла it.  I tried to reduce the gulf and the conflict between us by ла talking in order to unite our worlds.  Result : hysterical mess, ла blinding and blaming.

She denied having read it intentionally and ла said \the words just popped out through the enveloppe as the sun ла|was shining on it\". Hah Hah."|1|;;

column41: I feared that I would have to describe my sexual life to an ла older, strange woman.
When I moved away from home.

I had been guilty of gossiping and blaming others, and one of my ла superiors at the workplace made a formal reprimand.
When a student of mine (at music) performed and played remarkably well.
When climbing up the stairs to the top of a ski-jumping hill.
My boy-friend came home late one night without having told me ла about it before.
The breaking up of a long lasting relationship.

column41: When I noticed that a person I found attractive had seen me ла picking my nose.

While cycling in the country, I came across a large herd of ла cows.

When my friend did not pass the high school graduation ла examinations.

During lectures, I sensed an unexpressed understanding with a boy ла I did not know.  We exchange glances ; I think he likes me, and I ла like him too.  Perhaps he has fallen in love with me .........
At night, I walk home past a forest.  Once, somebody got stabbed ла in the forest.  I imagine someone attacking me and I hurry up.

In a tram, the ticket seller was commanding, taking the role of a ла leader, trying to emphasize her non-existent authority with undue ла strictness towards a good-humoured drunk who could not find his ла ticket at once.
A relationship in which I had put my trust, broke up.  I was sad ла when I realized how easy it is to forget something that one had ла once regarded as great and significant.
A nightmare.  I was dreaming about bloodsuckers, which I tried to ла shake off from my body, they are everywhere, they get glued, they ла suck.  And there are a lot of them.  I panic.
I told evil lies about a close friend of mine.  I was evil in ла order to sound jolly, to charm a person whom I wanted to impress. ла  I sold my friend, I was despicable.
I met my ex boyfriend by chance.  We separated a few months ago ла and I am now with a new boyfriend.  My ex boyfriend looked ла depressed, and I know I am not to be blamed.
[ During inter-rail-trip, after troubles, I met my little ла sister.]
Traveling as the only female in a railway carriage in the middle ла of the night in Italy.
A male, Honduran acquaintance of mine despised my opinions.
When our dog died.
While walking on the street with a good friend of mine, we met an ла acquaintance of hers.  My friend started showing off and telling ла false stories about herself and praising herself.
I was dishonest to my boyfriend concerning something that is ла important to our relationship.
A parking fine.
After having at last finished my master's thesis, I felt great ла joy and relief.  I had been haunted by the thesis during the ла whole of my studies.
While preparing my master's thesis, I was scared that I would not ла accomplish anything as the subject was rather difficult.

During the Summer, at my workplace, a person kept interfering ла with my tasks and making unfounded remarks.  I felt hatred for ла him but it stopped when I realized that he just longed for attention.
The last time I felt sad and disappointed was when I did not do ла as well as I had hoped in one of the final exams.  As compared ла with the earlier exams, the questions, I think, were unjust.
After the first of May, I detested my fiance's friends, who had ла piled on to our party and spoilt it completely.
After our sad first of May party, I felt ashamed because the ла friends who had been invited had to suffer.  We, the organizers ла of the party, did not drive the intruders away.

At my summer job, I was responsible for making various orders.  ла It was not me who had ordered some seasonal merchandise, but when ла much of it was left over and had to be thrown away in the Autumn, ла I felt partly responsible for the much too large order.
When I met a good friend of mine after a long time.
I was camping with a friend of mine and we spent the night in the ла forest.  I could not fall off to sleep and could clearly hear ла noises from outside (steps ?) approaching our tent.
When I quarelled with my parents.
Being away from a very close friend, I was away from Finland ла for a year as an exchange student.
When I saw a spider.
While playing I urinated on grandma's floor and did not go to the ла lavatory.  My cousin told grandma and she came.
While travelling in a bus with an invalid ticket, I got caught.
While having a discussion with a colleague of mine, I realized that her ла conception of man and work were similar to mine.
While he was drunk, my life partner tried to hit me.  I felt ла scared and fled to the bathroom.

column41: I could not meet my love, after having waited for a month, due to ла illness.
Once again, my life partner came back home drunk at midnight.
My love and me rented a room in a hotel one evening.  We stayed ла there a few hours and when leaving the hotel, I felt ashamed.
[ I had, by being silent, disapproved my love and made him ла unhappy.  He had not been able to keep his promise.  I thus was ла thinking about my own conduct towards another person.]
I had just moved to the town where I study and I got a postcard ла from a good friend (from my home town).

column41: They had returned much less of my taxes than I had expected.
After my boyfriend and I had separated.
In the morning, the cat of my landlady had vomited on the floor, ла near the staircase I take to go to the bathroom.
My boyfriend's mother, whom I had not met earlier, made an ла unexpected visit.  I was lying lazily on the bed, reading a ла newspaper and my boyfriend was studying.
The cat of my landlady escaped through the window which I had ла left open.
I got a letter from my best friend, whom I had not heard from for ла a long time (a good letter).

Someone knocked on the door when I was alone at home (though ла there was a door bell).  I looked through the peep hole but it ла had been covered.  I called my sister but she could not help me ла as she was hundreds of kilometres away.
My parents put pressure on me to buy clothes, when I would not ла have liked to do so.
When my grandfather died, I saw my grandmother crying against my ла aunt's shoulder (I had never seen my grandmother cry before).
At school, I detested the spinach gruel which had lumps of flour ла in it.
I told some acquaintances of mine something that I regretted ла later.
[ I speak harshly to my parents though they only mean my own ла good.]
When I got a letter from home.
While cycling in the country a dog started running beside me, ла growling and barking, and trying to bite my foot.
Disagreements with mother.  When I moved from KankaanpSS, she had ла promised to help me move but broke her promise because of some ла hindrance.
When I had to move away from home to study, and I knew that I ла would not be coming back home for a long time.
When I noticed two spiders running on the floor in different ла directions.
When I realized that I had been wrong about a person close to me, ла because of pre-set ideas and prejudices.
When I reproached my friend because I was myself low-spirited and ла disappointed.
I found myself a place after looking for one for a long time.
[ In an aeroplane.]
I was angry at my boyfriend who had promised to come to see me ла but did not because he spent the evening with his pals.
The breaking up of a relationship.  We decided that the ла relationship could not carry on, so it was no surprise to me. ла And anyhow, I had known it would happen sooner or later.
The disgust I feel towards a certain person.
After an event in which I felt that I had acted unfairly.
At my job, I got disproportionately angry with a child.  My ла reaction was not as it should have been.
I went to see the entrance examination results at university.  I ла rejoyced at my success.
I borrowed a car which was supposed to be used for a long journey ла a few hours later, and one of the tyres burst in the middle of ла the town and I did not know what to do.
An utterance, which I had intended to be a joke, was taken as an ла offence.  In my opinion, this was stupid, and I got angry.
My best friend had a relatively severe illness.  I was sad ла because she was suffering.
A man tried to have sexual intercourse with me, though I had ла communicated my unwillingness.  Later on, I felt disgust at that ла person as well as myself because I had partly submitted.
I told my friend about how I had calculated my salary by cheating a ла little.  When my friend remarked about it, I understood that it ла was wrong to do so, and I felt ashamed.
I am going steady with a boy, but I had sexual intercourse with ла another one, and I felt guilty about it afterwards.
A good report card (a scholarship) in primary school.
I was walking home with a friend at night along a quiet street.  ла Something started rustling in the bush : it was an exhibitionist.
I got angry at a friend of mine whom I caught reading my notebook ла (almanach).
When my grandmother died of cancer.
In a lift a drunken, fat and untidy man tried to make advances at ла me.
[ Sometimes I have by accident said to another person something ла in which it is easy to read a negative attitude.]
For the sheer pleasure of it, I quarelled with my boyfriend who was trying  ла to be especially kind to me.
When I made the acquaintance of a certain person.
When abroad, while driving a car along a dark, winding road.
When my sister took my things without having asked for my permission ла first.
When my grandfather died.
When I was working, I got treated in a way which I felt was not ла democratic.
While working as a domestic helper, one day I had not cleaned up ла very well and they made a remark about it.
When I decided to move away from my parent's home, my mother told ла me that it was as if a part of her had been torn out of her.
When I went to a job interview, I met a person who was very nice, ла and his attitude made me glad.
My episode of fright happened when I came to study.  I had to ла stand in front of my still unknown fellow students and talk about ла myself.  My hands shook, I flushed and became tongue-tied.

I felt guilty when I spent a night at my boyfriend's place, ла particularly because I had been harsh and spiteful when I had ла left home.  The reason was that I feared a possible discussion on ла the subject and I wanted to leave defiantly.
I was in a restaurant with my boyfriend when I saw my best female ла friend after not seeing her for two weeks.  We rejoyced, hugged ла and had a long talk.

One evening, while going to meet a friend of mine, I had to cross ла a meadow by a dark road.  There were bushes on the other side of ла the road.  The weather was damp and a bit foggy.  I heard steps ла behind me and kept speeding up my steps all the time.
My brother told me that a person (whom I know) had insulted him.  ла I am very fond of my brother, and as he himself can not get angry ла or hurt, my protectiveness was aroused and I got angry.

My guinea-pig had been ill for a couple of days.  One evening, ла when I came home I enquired as to how it was doing.  My mother's ла expression told me that it had died.  My knees refused to support ла me and I began to weep convulsively.
I happened to see two boys fighting, one of them fell down and ла hurt his head.  The other one used this to spank the head of the  boy on the ground.

I had been away all night without having told my parents about ла it.  In the morning when I came home, my mother looked tired.  ла She said that she had been awake all night because of me and that ла she was angry and disappointed.

I had not written to, or called my grandmother, who was lonely, ла for a long time.  My mother asked me to call her on her behalf ла and when I did so, my grandmother was delighted and she told me ла that she had been waiting for some news from us.
When I was sick my husband bought me a piece of cake.
I saw a man who had had a heart-attack and who was being ла treated for it.  I feared that my own father could have been ла there.
When I saw a big man hit another one, and nobody did anything.
When my sister left to go home, in Sweden, after the Christmas ла Holidays.
I feel guilty as I am not working, and even my studies are not ла progressing.
When my red-cheeked, content child runs to meet me in the yard of ла the kindergarten and gives me a moist kiss on my cheek.
A neighbour's girl had disappeared and many people were looking ла for her.  Someone had gone to notify the police.  Something had ла certainly happened to her.
Without my permission, my son had made popcorn after coming back ла from school.  The consequences were a spoilt kettle and chaos in ла the kitchen but what could have happened with the hot grease ?
The death of a close relative.
One of my fellow students used questionable and unfair means to ла advance her studies faster than others.  I detested her.
My friend told me in a fairly loud voice the blunders she ла committed last night.
I stopped my car in front of a pedestrian crossing as a child was ла crossing the street.  The car driving in the next lane did not ла stop and the child got hurt.  Had I not stopped ...

After my vacations, one day after a lecture it occured to me to ла buy a rose for my mother.  We went together to a pub and my ла mother told me that she would be getting married next Spring.  I ла did not known about it and so was all the more glad.

I work at a day care centre, and one day when the children were ла outdoors a four-year old boy disappeared from the yard.  I was ла not looking after them then, but as the manager it was me who was ла responsible.

Nevertheless, the very day I came back they ла called me early morining to ask me \what are you going to do ла|about the matter ?\" (which had been discussed in the meeting).  ла|Then I got angry."|1|;;

column41: The fact that my mother is getting married again (my mother and ла father divorced about 15 years ago) means that she will probably ла move to Turku, and our home, which is a one family house, will be ла sold (I myself have not been living at home for the past six ла years).

While travelling in a bus, there were three people sitting behind ла me (two men and a woman).  They were drunk and the conversation ла was unbelievable (about fucking, fellatio, etc...).  They tried ла to get others to take part in the conversation.  I loathed it and ла felt like crying.
When I was seven years old, I stole a chewing-gum from a big ла glass bowl on the counter of a nearby shop, and I got caught.
I am the secretary of an association, and during the last meeting ла I forgot to take the minutes.
I had been away from home for a long time and when I came home I ла was delighted.  It was wonderful to see familiar, dear people and ла I was rejoycing in advance.  I had been feeling very lonely.
I awoke at night and did not remember dreaming about antthing in ла particular.  I just felt oppressing fear, it was dark and all the ла others were sleeping.

One winter day I, unwillingly, was outdoors with my younger ла brother (10 years younger than me).  I lost my temper on him and ла wanted to throw my brother down the snow bank we were on.  I ла pushed him but not as hard as I had wanted to. We were alone the ла two of us.

At night my ла class mates prepared to clebrate their motive in life which was ла \life is merriment\".  I felt depressed about the way they sought ла|happiness."|1|;;

column41: I was on my way home by bus.  A man who had drunk a fair amount of ла alcohol started talking, trying to hug and pat a woman sitting ла next to him.  Fortunately it was not me.
I gave a wrong answer at school.
When my little brother asked me to play with him, I told him that ла I had no time and that I would play with him the next day. ла However, the next day I said the same thing.
When, after a long time, I saw a girl with whom I was in love.
When I was walking on a fairly out-of-the-way street.
A friend of mine had promised to arrange me some tickets for a ла concert which I considered important.  He could not get them the ла way he thought he would, so he gave up the whole thing.
I was sad when I saw that a beautiful girl was not attainable.

column41: While attending some affairs, which were taking some time, with ла a bank officer, I felt that my clothes and appearance were out of place, too ла raggy.
One evening I went out with some friends of mine, although I was ла supposed to stay at home with my little sister who is 11.
While watching an entertainment program in which there was a clever  ла and amusing sketch.
When I was in the army, a room mate of mine came back from ла furlough and threatened another fellow with a knife.
The last day of school is traditionally celebrated by singing a ла song about all the students who are leaving.  In the song ла about me, there were things which irritated me a lot.
I worked for seven months in a factory, and made friends with a ла fellow worker.  Later, I visited my former fellow workers and was ла told that, while in the army, my friend had shot himself.
The behaviour of a fellow towards me and some others in the army ла was really mean.  I detested this.
I tried to date a girl, but she refused.
While doing some calculation exercises, I neglected a part of it, ла though I had marked it as done.  By chance, I was asked to ла demonstrate this very part on the blackboard.
In the army, my result at the shooting exercises got ла me a three day furlough.

When I was 8 years old, I would usually come home from school ла with my mother in a car.  For the first time I had to take the ла school bus, and I mistook the bus stop and found myself two ла kilometres away from where I lived.  I was very scared, wondering ла how I would get back home.

I read in the newspaper that the Student Lodging Fund was going ла to build new appartments for refugees (in my opinion this is the ла state's affair).  This is when only a fractoin of the students ла can find an appartment.
I lead a rather secure life.  The only thing I can remember is a ла song from the nineteenth century which is against alcohol.  Both ла the melody and the word (although naive) effected my emotions.
Yesterday in the elevator a man started smoking, this is ла something I just can not tolerate.
In primary school I once faltered while answering a question and ла the others started laughing.
[ Generally when I am shopping I feel like I were guilty of all ла the thefts through the year (I have never stolen).]
When my favourite football team made a goal and was about to ла win the Cup of England.
I was less than 10 years old when our neighbour's dog chased me ла to the roof of a small shed and there seemed to be no hope of ла getting away from there.
While playing a ball game, I was just about to make a goal when I ла was thrown off my feet, and I failed to score the goal.
When I heard about the death of Frantois Truffaut, the French motion  ла picture director, on the radio.  I had planned to go and see his ла last film.

column41: I had misbehaved at a party and did not wish to meet the person ла in question later.
While playing a ball game, I made a mistake and we lost the game.
When I was in the sauna bath.

When my car froze, and I could not start it.
When I saw our computer teacher.
When I was going downhill on skis, and fell down twice the first ла time.
When I was involved in a car crash.

When my grandmother died of cancer.
When I was still a child, I saw a horror film on TV in which ла there was a rotten human skull.
As a small boy, I took a coin from an empty taxi cab.  My mother ла saw it and told the driver about it.  I even knew the driver.
When I betrayed my former girlfriend.

New Year's Eve party in the country, I hardly knew a person; my ла partner spent most of the time at the bar. I had little ла opportunity to get to know people because our table was separated ла and my boyfriend's parents were present.
Christmas Eve: there was a tension between my parents, they did ла not even try to restore a harmonic atmosphere. Mother stayed in ла her room almost the whole day. I felt alone and was very sad.
Father said: If you are pregnant, you will have to procure ла abortion. I was filled with disgust against my father.
I had an intimate relation with my boyfriend, but unfortunately ла we had sexual problems; therefore I deceived him, but I was ла ashamed when I told my friend about it.
I work at a commercial house from 7 to 10 a.m. On a very cold day ла in winter I was late - and let a fellow worker stand in the cold ла for half an hour.
After one year of searching, my friend and I have found a flat we ла are able to pay for.
Car accident in the middle of the night.
At the weekend I wanted to be absent from school because of a ла sports event, but my teacher refused to give me the day off ла because he didn't like me.
When I was six years old, my favourite cat died.
A gigantic spider climbed over my face and what is more - in my ла own flat.
I was very fat and felt absolutely unwell. I was afraid of ла leaving the house and getting to know new people.
I was said to be responsible for my mother getting ill and ла growing thin. I did not realize that it really was my fault until ла several weeks later.
I won a car in a prize-competition. The moment I was informed ла about it, I felt joy.

Recent break-up of seriors long-term relationship, helped along ла by would-be  in-laws.

column41: After failing a second attempt at Med 4, following a number of ла difficult personal circumstances.
Failure to complete medical course as a result of failing fourth ла year twice.
When Wayne and Sue (close friends) were announced our guardians ла at ther wedding.
Car accident nearly occurred between us and drunk driver coming ла in opposite direction it missed us by approx 1 m and collided ла (after rolling twice midair) into nearby scrub.
When boyfriend lied to me.
When my boyfriend took me to his father's grave.
On boat trip - saw mother giving young child (aprox 6-7 years) ла cigarettes.
When harassed by this boy - it was sexual (refer to GUILT).
When in grade 3, late home from school every day for weeks ла because of harassment from a grade 7 boy I lied to mother about ла why I was home late.
Getting a part-time job.
Small car accident. Black ice on the road - cars in front of us ла started zig-zagging and so did we. Car in front did a 180Е_ turn we ла followed and ended up in a gully.
People hunting animals.
When my grandfather was sick, and died I felt more sad, though, ла when he was sick.
People spitting in railway stations.
Falling over.
Eating too much I felt guilty afterwards because I knew I ла shouldn't have overeaten as I'm putting on too much weight.
When my last year's second semester results came through - I was ла ecstatic.
I was sleeping in my room but woke in the middle of the night to ла think I could hear noises and see shadows moving. I felt that ла someone was in the house.
At school, a couple of years ago, a so-called acquaintance told lies ла about me to a teacher I was told about it by friends who overheard ла the conversation.

My grandfather died. He lived almost as a recluse not caring for ла himself as well as he should - Dad and we all helped as much as ла we could, but it didn't save him from himself. It was an ла unexpected death. His second de facto wife was lucky she wasn't ла jailed.
In my penultimate job I was responsible of a sections with ла several employers, after several years of dedication I was ла dismissed by a new chef, saying that I was incompetent.
I assisted to a scene where the police attacked a person that ла didn't have his documents. The savagery was too much, and the ла attacked person bleeded to much.
In a party of friends I got completely drunk.
Once in my homes yard, I was plaing football with my cousin and ла in a certain quick the ball went on uncontrolled putting down a ла bird-cage, killing it.
When I get something that seemed very hard like getting a job, a ла boyfriend, etc. A specific sutuations, was when I started to date ла a boy whom I liked for a long time.
When I had to assume a position which I didn't expect.
When I was dismissed unjustly from the firm where I worked, ла because there where persons that didn't have problems, and ла wouldn't miss in the jobs they occupied if they were dismissed.
I felt very sad when I had to give up something that by right was ла mine and although I didn't get it, a kind of suvenir that people ла don't give you the right to have.
The acts of brutal violence in generally disgusts me. Fights, ла phisical aggrssion, etc.
I felt ashamed when in a certain occasion I had to read a text ла and didn't stop stuttering.
When I was reproved eighth grade of high school.
When I talked with a teacher yesterday who, to say the least, was ла rude and unwise and had irrelevant opinions about a friend.
The loss of the woman who loved me most till today.
In a sexual experience with an unknown woman where after the ла sexual act I only could go away without looking backwards.
When I wanted to kiss a friend and didn't succeed, I felt shame.
On a telephone talk where I was agressive and stupid without the ла least, reason or better motive.
When I succeed in writing something I felt and doing it I felt ла well and very happy for being able to express to myself something ла that was suffocating me.
When I crashed my car.
When in a difficult moment I couldn't express myself correctly ла and my thought came out with distortions bringing about highly ла negative and distorted results.
When I heard about the death of somebody I liked very much and I ла was not present either to see the person or to try to share my ла emotions with other friends.

When I saw a woman subjugated by money and not being able to hide ла how she hated herself for not having the will power to get out of ла such a situation because it was convenient, according to what she ла told me.
When somebody suddenly said something (about me) at a wrong ла moment and I didn't agree (at that exact moment I was needing an ла extremely positive word).
When my mother surprised me while masturbating.
I forgot to water the flowers in our flat and was rebuked by my ла friends who share the flat with me.
After my final examination at school I was glad that the ла examination was over and that I had passed it.

When I was a child, I had a nightmare. At that time, I was not ла yet able to tell anybody about it, so I was very frightened. I ла could not explain myself all that and I had to deal with it by ла myself.
I was angry with a person who behaved terribly at a ball ла offending her relatives.
When my grandfather died. When I heard about his death, I had a ла bad feeling in my stomach and I felt as if I had lost something ла very precious.
My brother caught a spider and let his frog eat it.
Once I spoke without thinking very much - it was quite a ла nonsense.
I was not sure whether I should help an old woman going down a ла flight of stairs. I just watched her and saw how difficult it was ла for her to do it.
For about one year I had a rather bad relation with my father. ла Last Christmas Eve he invited me to stay withhim and I was very ла glad about it. It was a fine evening.

I live outside Graz - so I have to go by bus. One day I went home ла from the bus stop alone. It was dark, I had to go through a ла forest and there was a dark figure behind me. I was very ла frightened.
My sister had promised to help me to do a translation from ла English into German. But the day I needed her she told me that ла she was busy - I was very angry.
Several years ago my mother died. She had been ill for a long ла time, but nevertheless her death came unexpectedly. I did not and ла I still do not want to believe that it is true.
I have a horror of spiders and snakes. On a walk through the wood ла I saw the body of a slow-worm (without the head).
I came home from a party rather drunk. I said things I would ла never have said normally. Next morning I was terribly ashamed ла about what I had said.
An accident happened to my little cousin because I had not taken ла enough care of her. She fell on the floor and her hands were ла hurt.

I had a little cat which was very sick. As I liked it very much I ла went to a veterinary with it. He told me how to tend it and it ла really recovered its health. Everybody said that I had saved its ла life.

When I was a child, I had a terrible nightmare with St. Nicholas' ла Devil Servant. I asked my mother if he really existed and she ла said yes. The following nights I could not sleep and a ла light had to be left turned on.
As I usually do not start learning until a short time before an ла examination,, I once made up my mind to try to work for a longer ла time. But once again I did not do it - and got a bad mark.

A friend told me about his cousin who is my girlfriend. He said ла she had treated him in a mean and nasty way. I was surprised ла because in front of other people she had always treated him in a ла friendly way. I am very sad about it.
I went out with my sister, her boyfriend and his friend. I did ла not like this young man. But suddenly he overcame me and kissed ла me. He was very strong so that I could not defend myself.
During the oral part of my final examination I made a mistake in ла speaking so that all the teachers laughed at me.
There was a time when I did not get on well with my sister. I ла always grumbled at her and said bad things about her to my ла mother. So my mother always scolded her.
When I passed my final examination at school.
When I was on a cave excursion with friends, I suddenly lost them ла and was afraid of losing my way in the cave.
When I felt being treated unjustly by a teacher.
When my grandmother died; I had a stronger relation to her than ла to my mother.
When I was molested by an old drunk man.
When I had a Latin examination in school.
When I had drunk too much and nearly got an alcohol poisoning.
When I met my girlfriend again in another town after a long ла separation.
When I went home alone early in the morning, I had to go through ла a wood.
A friend was unpunctual, we wanted to prepare ourselves for an ла examination.
When my grandparents moved to another part of the town.
At the butcher's I saw an animal which had just been slaughtered; ла blood was dripping on the floor.
In school I was very bad in running long distances and my ла class-mates laughed at me for this reason.
I had to take care of my little brother. When I met a friend I ла did not pay attention to him for a certain time and he was hurt ла while he was playing.
On my birthday, an old friend of mine sent me a card. I had not ла met him for a year and I was very glad that he had thought of me.
Once I spent a night with a friend at the secondary school. We ла told each other horror stories and suddenly we heard uncanny ла noises. I was terribly frightened.

When we still attended school, my brother and I usually went to ла see our aunt and to show her our term's report. She rewarded us ла with money. Although my reports were as good as my brother's, he ла got more money.
My friend was pregnant, but lost her child during the second ла month. I went to see her at hospital - she was crying. I felt ла very sorry for her.
When I attended school, our class visited an institution for ла mentally and physically handicapped persons. Although I tried to ла control my feelings, I was disgusted.
After a party I spent the night with a friend. We both were ла drunk, the morning was disillusioning. A friend was me leaving ла the room and I felt shabby and immoral.
I had to take care of a neighbour's child. I did not look after ла it all the time and the child fell down and was hurt. I felt ла guilty.
A very good friend of mine had been away for three months. When ла we met again, we ran up to each other and embraced.

One evening my father told me to go into the cellar and get him a ла beer. I was terribly frightened at the idea of a man sitting in ла the cellar and assaulting me. For my defence I took an empty ла bottle with me.
I had stolen a bottle of rum from a person who knows me well. He ла threatened to call the police if I did not pay 500 Shillings.
When my uncle died I saw a funeral for the first time. All people ла stood around the open grave and cried.
At a party I met a girl who drew me to her, told me some nonsense ла and always wanted to kiss me.
I put my head into the pullover of a girl to see her breasts. The ла girl looked at me so that I felt ashamed.

My uncle had promised to buy me a bicycle. As time went by and I ла had not received it yet, I asked my father to buy it for me. ла Later I heard that my uncle had wanted to offer me the bicycle on ла my birthday two weeks later.
Several days after my final examination at school, I was sitting ла in an airplane on my way to Greece. I enjoyed that moment very ла much.

One night I was lying in my bed awake but I had my eyes closed. I ла saw figures with terrible faces and black frocks bending over me ла and touching me. I opened my eyes but I could still see them. I ла had the feeling that somebody was in the room. It was terrible. ла Only when I turned on the light I was able to go to sleep.

I had arranged with a friend to go with him to Carinthia by car. ла We had arranged a place where to meet. I was a bit late and my ла friend had left already. I had no money to go by train. I nearly ла started to cry because I was so angry - it was very important for ла me to go to Carinthia.
Our dog had to be shot because he had killed a roe. I liked him ла very much and so I could not resign myself to that. I hated the ла hunter who shot him.

I was sitting in a station-hall and watching a lavatory ла attendant. She was very dirty. She started to eat something out ла of a dirty cup - it must have been something like lard. Then she ла took some breadcrumbs out of the pockets of her apron and ate ла them. I had to leave - I felt like vomitting.
I had to go to the doctor's because of a veneral disease. I told ла the doctor that I must have been infected by my boy-friend. This ла was not true, but I was ashamed to tell the truth.
When we were playing, I hurt my little sister, but towards my ла mother I did not admit that it was my fault.
My neighbour was not able to set his car in motion because it had ла snowed heavily. I helped him - he was thankful and invited me.
I was skiing with friends and they wanted to ski-jump. I did not ла want to be left behind, so I braced myself and followed them.
At an examination I got a bad mark just because of a small ла mistake. When I went to the lector and wanted to talk about that, ла he did not listen to me but sent me away.
My cut was run over by a car. After searching for a long time I ла found her lying in a kerb. I was rather shocked and angry with ла the driver.
When I watched a report about El Salvador on TV, I saw people who ла had been murdered by terrible methods.
At a cross-country race I wanted to take a short-cut (which is ла not allowed). I was caught and disqualified. All my friends had ла observed that.
During a discussion I reacted very aggressively and so I made it ла impossible to continue discussing.
On my birthday I got a present that I had desired for a long ла time.
When I am discussing something with a person and I realize that ла the other person is thinking over her own argumentations instead ла of listening, I become angry.
When we were on holidays my girl-friend had to leave me after 4 ла weeks and I had to stay in Turkey for some more weeks because I ла had a job there.
I studied medicine for several semesters. I was always disgusted ла when we had the dissecting-course. I cannot understand why some ла persons like this course.

Some time ago we had a tournament in our tennis-club. For ла tactical reasons I was chosen to play against a much weaker ла player than I am. Although it would have been enough simply to ла win the game, I defeated him extremely. This would not have been ла necessary.

I had a discussion with my girl-friend. After some time we ла started to quarrel and at least - to get the upper hand - I said ла that she was not as important to me as she might believe. Some ла time later I apologized for that.
On New Year's Eve I went in a disco with friends. I amused myself ла and got to know many other people.
I had to go to the dentist's. When he touched my tooth with his ла drill, I was terribly aftaid of the pain I would feel any moment.
I was very hungry and just wanted to start eating when a friend ла called me who usually talks for a long time. I was angry because ла I was prevented from eating.
My sister, whom I like very much, asked me for a favour which I ла refused her for some flimsy reason. Some time later I felt sorry ла for that and something like sadness.
On my way to a concert I went with a man who tried to molest me. ла At that moment I did not care much but now the impression fills ла me with disgust.

I asked my friend to come with me to a disco because I wanted to ла be with a person I know well. But when I amused myself with ла others I let my friend sit alone, although I had asked her to ла come.

I called my little sister to make her pick up her toy from the ла floor. When she still refused after I had asked her for the ла fourth time, we began to quarrel. At last the whole family was ла involved in this quarrel and trouble was brewing.
I had a singing-lesson, but I was not very good. The last ла exercise was singing scales. I did that very well and my teacher ла seemed satisfied.
A teacher wanted to instill a certain opinion and a certain ла behaviour into myself, what I refused. I was afraid when I saw ла him.
A friend had promised to call me at a certain time. I expected ла his call impatiently but in vain.
Years ago on Christmas Eve I felt very sad because I realized for ла the first time how I missed my father who had died at Christmas ла Years ago.
A man whom I like, was drunk and tried to molest me.

It was the time when everybody spoke about and discussed ла Hainburg. I was also asked for my opinion. I was ashamed because ла I had no firm view of the whole thing and therefor was not able ла to join the conversation.

column41: On my 18th birthday I passed the driving-test. I was glad because ла I had had to study very much, because I had been lucky and ла because - as a proof that it was really difficult - not everybody ла had passed the test.

At about midnight I had to go by bike through Graz alone. On the ла whole it was a distance of several kilometers. A car followed me ла through the streets. Only when I went into a one-way street the ла car disappeared. The rest of my way home I was very afraid.

I had studied for almost one week for my physics-examination. ла With difficulty I passed the examn. I was angry about the teacher ла and also about myself because I had not remembered enough during ла the examn and because the time that I spent studying was wasted.
I had cared for a horse for 2 years. One day it was sold and I ла cried for several days because I was so sad.
A friend of mine was telling jokes which I felt to be very ла disgusting, especially because I was eating.
At a carneval-party I smooched with a man - some days later I was ла rather ashamed for that.
By fun I had a tussle with my sister. Suddenly I obviously hurt ла her unintentionally - and she ran out of the room, crying.

During my first week in Graz I met a girl who I had got to know ла in the train from Amsterdam to Graz. Although I had considered ла her very sympathetic, we had seperated without changing our ла adresses.

column41: I had got a bad cold. My father said I must be crazy to go by ла motorbike at those temperatures. When I answered him that I did ла not care about a cold, he said that if I did not care for ла anything I could leave him (it was for the second time he said ла something like that).

I was at home alone when I realized that a young roe approached ла our house. I hid because I did not want to frighten it. It ла limped. Some time later, when I thought that it had already run ла away, I saw it lying on our terrace. I came nearer and saw that ла it was terribly wounded. I informed the ranger who said that the ла roe must have been attacked by dogs. He had to shoot it.

Several years ago I stayed with friends in the mountains for one ла week. We lived in a hut and had to cook for ourselves. One day my ла friend did not succeed in preparing spaghetti. That dinner was ла terrible - nevertheless we all ate rather much and had an ла improper and unsavoury conversation.

My mother and my grandmother were talking about one of my ла grandmother's friends whom I hardly know. I gave some deprecatory ла comments on him whereupon my grandmother told me that the man had ла died recently.

When I still went to primary-school, I went on a ski-trip with my ла family. After skiing we went to a restaurant for lunch. Suddenly ла my father said that he had forgotten something in the car. He ла gave me the key and asked me to go and get it. I had difficulties ла with the key which was already bent. I asked my mother to help ла me. When she tried to turn the key it broke. We had no second ла key. My mother was blamed for all that and I did not say a word.

I had not studied very much for my final examination at school, ла so I had to take an additional examination in French. The oral ла examination was not very hard for me - the more I was glad when I ла heard that I had passed it.
When I was 8 years old my tonsils had to be operated on. This is ла not a complicated operation, but just before it started I was ла very afraid so that I will never forget it.

My parents are divorced, father pays alimony for me. Two years ла ago my sister who lives with father, suddenly asked mother for ла money. As she considered the amount of money my mother offered ла her too small, she brought an action against mother. I was ла terribly angry with my sister.

I arranged with a friend to go skating the next day. He asked me ла to wake him up by telephone at twelve o'clock because we had come ла home late in the morning. Next day I called him - he was not at ла home. As something like that had happened to me several times ла before, I came to the conclusion that one cannot rely on anybody ла and I felt very sad.
Whenever I see a spider or a snake I feel disgusted.

When I had slept with a boy for the first time I felt ashamed for ла three reasons. First, because I was only 13 years old, second, ла because I did not really like him, third, because he had caught ла me napping.

I had been together with my boy-friend for two and a half years, ла when he got to know another girl and not even tried to conceal ла that from me. I drew my conclusions and left him - I also felt a ла bit guilty for what had happened.
My boy-friend told me that he would take me to the training of ла the life-saving dogs.
I was in a dark cellar and saw a glowing red point. I thought ла that it was a person with a cigarette - but it was only the red ла switch.
A man treated his dog very badly - he insulted and beated him ла until the dog kept lying on the floor with his tail drawn in.
A horse which I had liked very much was taken away.
On TV I saw a report about church in Amerika. A priest was shown ла who was performing miracles in front of the camera - I felt ла disgusted.
When I was a child, my uncle came to see us. I spit at him and ла ran out - I do not know the reason for that. My father came after ла me and insisted on my apologizing.
I quarreled with my boy-friend. He said it was unfair that I ла always started crying so that he had to give in.

To be able to prepare myself better for an important examination, ла I did not spend the nitht with my girl-friend but in the ла students' hostel. I had not done that for months. The day when I ла had the examn, somebody knocked at my door at seven o'clock in ла the morning. My girl-friend who likes sleeping late, had come to ла be able to be with me.

I studied medicine for several semesters and at that time I ла developed a great fear of examinations. I was most afraid of my ла examination of anatomy. While other students were examined, I was ла dissecting. I was able to hear everything and was waiting with ла fear until it was my turn.

When I come home in the evening, the first thing I do is to sit ла down and smoke a cigarette. One day I found the flat in a totally ла desolate state. My girl-friend had wanted to tidy up but had not ла finished.

My son's mother told me that she wanted to move to Vienna and ла take the child with her. This means a rather long distance for ла me. My whole family was sad and dumbfounded so that my own ла feelings were intensified.
When a very near person got into an awkward situation but showed ла only helplessness and indecision.
I spent an evening with my girl-friend. When we wanted to go to ла bed I was totally drunk. Next morning I felt rather ashamed.
I threw away an object, which belonged to a friend, because I did ла not know what to do with it. My friend was very sad about that ла and I felt guilty.
After a long time I saw my boy-friend again.
My first public appearance in front of a rathe big audience.
I was angry about how the government acted concerning Hainburg, ла especially when I saw a discussion about it on TV.
Death of my father; he died of laryngeal cancer.
When I got indecent offers.
When I bought new skis; I was ashamed to tell the assistant that ла I am not good at skiing and therefor bought racing skis.
My schoolmates were teasing a pupil who was not able to defend ла himself very well; I should have taken his part.
I thought that I had failed an examination, but when I was ла informed about the mark, I saw that I had passed it.
Before an examination: I had the fealing that I had not learned ла enough.
Once when I was playing table tennis I was already sure that I ла would win , but at last I lost the game.
My grandfather's funeral.
In cinema I saw a film which showed how a person was torn out his ла guts when he was still alive.
I was sitting in a restaurant with friends. They asked me ла something which they thought I should know. Actually I know it, ла but at that time I was not able to remember it.
I had an appointment with a friend. I promised him to meet with ла him, but at last I did not without having informed him.
When I had a psychical crisis, I met a girl, who told me that she ла had had almost the same problems and how she had finally overcome ла them.

I had climbed on a cherry tree alone and there was a thick ла caterpillar beside my fingers. I feel disgusted by caterpillars ла and snakes. I was terribly afraid of the caterpillar crawling on ла my fingers. Out of the fear I was almost unable to climb down.
A friend of mine told other people that I was a slattern (because ла of an occurence that had happened some time ago). When I heard ла about that I was very angry.

My grandfather was seriously ill, he had only a few days left to ла live. I had always loved him, but never told him. When I saw him ла for the last time, I had the feeling that I had omitted so many ла things I could not do again. - There was a fly sitting on his ла forehead and he was too weak to drive it away. I was very sad ла when I saw that.

Normally my father never tells vulgar jokes, we do not speak ла about sexual things, too. But once he told such a vulgar joke, ла that I was really disgusted. He did not tell me, but some of his ла friends, but I was present.

When I was 6 or 7 years old, I pulled down the trousers of a ла friend because I wanted to know what she looked like. My mother ла watched that and (as a punishment) sent me into the house. We ла never spoke about that; I think it was as embarassing for her as ла it was for me.

When I told my boy-friend, who loved me very much, that I wanted ла to put an end to our relationship. a long time before I told him ла that and also a long time after that I felt guilty, because I had ла hurt him so much.
Unexpectedly I met some persons who I like very much. ла Spontaneously they invited me and integrated me within their ла group, although it was late in the evening.

After a footballmatch I went home by car, a friend drove. I did ла not realize that he was drunk until we were in the car. He was ла madly racing. Several times we were in dangerous situations and I ла told him to be cautious, but he did not care.

A friend of mine uses butter instead of oil when he is cooking. I ла am always angry about that, because it is an unnecessary luxury. ла Recently we both were cooking and he wanted to use butter again. ла When I had already put the oil into the pan, he poured it out ла again and put the butter into the pan.
After some friends had come to see me. They had stayed for ла several days and we had got on very well. When they had left, I ла had a feeling of emptyness.

I had a quarrel with a friend who lived with me in the same flat. ла He moved out. Before he went he invited me and some friends for a ла drink. At last he was totally drunk and smelled disgusting. ла Besides, he told lies about us and behaved as if he was to be ла pitied.

I went to see a friend. There were other people, too, and ла everybody brought some present. I was the onlyone who brought ла nothing. My friend was very hospitable and did not show anything ла - although I knew how he felt.

With a group of handicapped people we went to a party. When we ла wanted to leave we were not able to find one of these people. I ла had told his mother that we would leave at 4.30 p.m., actually it ла was planned for 3.30 p.m. Therefore there was a delay.
I had a quarrel with my fiancT. When he admitted his fault, ла everything was allright. It was then for the first time that he ла surprised me with coffee and cake and a bunch of flowers.
After my boy-friend had beaten me for the first time, I always ла trembled when somebody knocked on my door or when I heard steps ла coming nearer.
I had not eaten anything for 2 days to be able to pay the fine ла for my fiancT. But he stayed in another town and spent one ла thousand shillings in the restaurant during the same time.
I had to give up my love, because it did not work out well.
I was insulted without a reason by a drunk man.
My boyfriend had drunk too much and beaten me. When I had to show ла the letter the door, which was almost crashed, I felt ashamed.
I spied on my fiancT and was terribly jealous. Later I saw that ла there was no reason for that.
My sister had a daughter. I saw the baby for the first time ла through a pane of glass and she looked at me.

My mother, my sister and I were sitting in the sitting room and ла watching a film on TV. My father came home drunk and told us to ла turn off. When we did not do that he switched off the fuse and ла started shouting. We were sitting in the dark and I was afraid ла that he would do us a harm.

I wanted ла to arrive before them and went on a shorter, but more dangerous ла way. When I arrived, I found nobody there. I waited for a long ла time, but nobody came. On my way back I met my mother who had ла been searching for me desperatly. She did not scold me, but I saw ла how much she had worried (herself).

column41: When we had swimming instruction, we had to take a header from ла the springboard. I usually refused to do that, but at least I was ла forced to.

column41: I stayed for several weeks with a friend of mine before she moved ла to live with her husband. One evening he came drunk and made an ла awful scene, which I still remember.

But ла she had an audience and was in one of those moods. Once I'd ла accepted it was something everyone does at time I felt better - ла it was partly having my friend there.

I sensed such a feeling when I understood I was admitted to the ла University. I was at home, the atmosphere was still, though I ла myself was full of suspense. I tried to do different things. This feeling I sensed quite recently. It was arisen by the ла terrific thought that I might lose the man I loved !

Sometimes, when I'm alone I am seized by this feeling. But it ла always helps me to come round and at the same time to judge if it ла is worth. Very often this feeling is caused to me by people - ла friends who I love and respect.

When I was admitted to the University.

Always, and this happens often when I do not keep my word.
When I understood that I was admitted to the University.

A quarrel was followed by the decision of leaving a person close ла to me. Several days later my regret was great. I was beside ла myself. Quite unexpectedly he came and the conflict was calmly ла solved. I was glad at the possibility to be with him.

When I understood I was admitted to the Sofia University.

column41: The doctors from Belogradchik town determined a wrong diagnosis ла to my son. A month later, after some complex examinations at ISUL ла (A medical institute in Sofia), the diagnosis was categorically rejected.

When I pass exams, or when a close friend of mine recovered ла from an illness,etc.
Fights that I see in the middle of the street, robberies, fear of ла darkness when going home.
During a family discussion on my future and my prospects as a ла student, they accused me of not bothering about looking for a job to ла assume my financial situation.
[ Depressions.]
Some people whom I do not like at all, and one of the reasons is ла their physical appearance.
For example, to feel bad because of one's attire, to be among ла people who do not belong to the same social class, to give a ла wrong answer in class, to be surprised in particular situations.
Some of my friends had an argument.  I had earlier phoned one ла of them and that may have influenced him to argue.
When I met a very close friend of mine after one year of ла separation.
There was an earthquake for several minutes and I was on the ла eight floor.
An argument among several friends because of the irrational ла behavior of one of them who fell out with us for no reason and ла said that we were to blame.
A class-mate died after being two months in coma, after a car ла accident.
Pictures of Nazi extermination camps on a T.V program.
Equivocal situation when filling a security questionnaire on ла entering a government building with several people there.
I left a boy with whom I was going around without giving him any ла explanations.
When my sister was born.
When they tried to rob me.

When my grandmother died.

When my little sister was born.

When a professor of this faculty laughed at, and was suspicious of ла a composition written by a class-mate and me.
The death of a relative, friend, or someone I esteem.
When I saw a very disagreable scene.
When I had to represent my boss at a meeting.

When a class-mate died.

I had an exam and I had it well prepared.  I did the first part ла very well but did not know the second part.
When my parents did not let me go on a study tour.
One day I was going through the street door of my house, when a ла man asked me for a doctor.  He then showed me his genitals and ла asked me to cure him myself.
Each time the professor asks me a question in class.

An invitation to spend 5 days at the seaside with all expenses ла paid.
A film on zombies.

When I see pornographic films.

When a friend of mine was beaten for what was my fault.

An old woman was violently thrown down the stairs of the tube by ла a group of louts.
A child, 9 years old, died in a stupid way.  He fell from a place ла which was 1 metre high.

Before knowing my marks I was not sure that I wanted to go to ла that class.

I was in the cafeteria at the university and a class-mate told me ла that a friend of hers had had all her teeth taken out because of ла an infection caused by her eating a rat's nail in her hamburger.

One night, after having decided to finish our relationship, I ла took my girlfriend home.  While driving back home, I felt that I ла had not handled the whole thing very well.
The begining of my relations with my current girlfriend.
When I am alone at night after having read horror stories, and ла then I heard unexplainable noises.
A typical family argument.
The disqualification of two of my mates in the military service.

When criticizing something about a person and then realizing that ла the person whom one is talking to is similar.
Not to have studied enough when exams were near.
When I pass an exam.
Continous fear of a nuclear war.
When you kill yourself with work and see the number of slakers ла wandering around, doing nothing.
When someone in my family died.
To loose friends because of them over-estimating themselves.
