I thought that I was going to fail a subject and so I began to ла study for the final exam, then my friend told me that I had ла passed it.  That meant that I could go home, as I do not study in ла my hometown.
I was in Sierra Nevada, climbing a peak over 3,000 metres high, ла without any light and with many other problems.  I was afraid for ла my life.
I was living in a flat where things did not go very well for me.  ла Finally, they threw me out and this prejudiced people I esteem a ла lot.
When I read the diary of the girl with whom I was living, it was ла about another boy with whom she had been going around some time back.
The man who threw me out of the flat disgusted me.
The first time that I caressed a girl, I was about thirteen and ла she was eighteen.  I noticed that it did not affect her at all.
I was going around with a girl without loving her.  Not only did ла I go around with her, but we did many more things.  In the end I ла was not very sincere to her.
I met a girlfriend again after not seeing her for several months. ла  I saw her in a discotheque.  We do not like discotheques but we ла went there because we knew we would meet there.
I was walking in the countryside alone when I came across two ла dogs who began barking at me.  I did not know whether they were ла tied up or loose, but I was afraid of them approaching me.

I was angry when my sister began to talk nonsense and to laugh at ла the way I swept the room.  My anger grew (I tried to control ла myself).  After telling her to leave me alone, I vented my anger ла on her as she did not obey me.
My mother was working with a knife and we were all laughing ла heartily.  She was not able to control the knife and stuck it ла deep into her hand.
I read a book whose plot and expressions were obscene and in very ла bad taste.
My mother had just been teaching me how to crochet, which is ла thought highly improper for a boy in a town.  Just when we ла finished, a neighbour walked in.

It was about midnight and I wanted to go to the countryside (I ла was in town) to watch the stars in the sky.  My mother did not ла like this, in spite of it I went out for a while.  My mother got ла angry.
A friend of mine suggested that I become a film extra.  The idea ла seemed very funny to me and my reaction seemed rather outlandish ла to the others.
One day I went to the cinema to see a film in which I was ла interested.  On arriving there I saw a long queue (which I had ла not expected) and went back home without seeing the film.
When I miss the train and I am late, and I have to wait half an ла hour for the next one.
When I knew I had to go out with my mother on some errands.

One day in class, the professor asked me a question concerning something ла he had been explaining.  He was very close to me (beside me) and I ла had no idea what to answer.
Once I had some homework to do and I did not do it.
When they phoned me from Great-Britain to tell me that I could go ла there, if I wished, in Summer.
When I was operated on the knee and had to go through rehabilitation.
In a very important basket-ball match where a lot was at stake, I ла played very badly.
When a friend of mine told me that he was going to commit ла suicide.
A TV program on whale-hunting.
Once when I said bad things concerning a friend.
Family discord and uneasiness due to something I did not ла communicate on time.
When I passed my driving test, as it was the fifth time that I ла had taken this test.
When my mother was robbed in a shop.
I was given an exam which I thought did not measure at all my ла ability or my knowledge of the subject.

column41: Some friends and I were having lunch.  Someone said something ла funny and one of the guys started laughing and spat his food in a girl's ла face.

When they told me that my grandfather was rather ill.

When, after drinking a glass of water, I found a cockroach walking ла out of the glass.

I have a very close friend who lives in another city and we have ла been writing to each other for a long time.  The last time I went ла to her city, just to see her, I was disappointed to see how great ла the distance between us was.

The girl with whom I was going around had been forbidden to be ла alone with me in the house.  We paid no attention to this ла prohibition but one day her parents appeared and I jumped out of ла the window.  They saw me.

Every time, in the last few days, when my girlfriend told me that ла she loves me.

We were at school, in the room for audiovisual classes.  We were ла watching a film, and just behind me two classmates were bothering ла me with their mocking and shoves.  I reacted angrily (I suppose)  ла by hitting one of them.
[ During a summer holiday a French girl and I had becoe back ла home, I felt very sad.]
Once I had to clean a lavatory which was obstructed.  It was in a ла friend's country house and there was nobody there to help me.
In a Mathematics class, the professor asked me a question and I ла gave the wrong answer.

A party I went to last Christmas.
When my mother had a nervous illness.
During my last exam.
When I had to come back from my village last Christmas.
One day I went to see a rather disagreeable film (X).

When a close classmate failed a year.
I was talking to a friend and he said something which was very ла funny.

In a confrontation with a person, he provoked me several times ла till I reacted in an angry way.  Fortunately there were no ла disastrous consequences.

When I do or say something inappropriate which hurts people close ла to me.
When a study tour got confirmed, I was happy all the time till    ла the tour began.
I was walking down a road and suddenly a few dogs appeared at a fence ла and started barking angrily.  They were jumping and it seemed ла that they would come for me any time.

In an exam when I answered the questions with very little ла assurance due to insufficiet preparation.

I was at the table at a French friend's house.  They served me a ла big dish with roast cauliflower and sauce.  I had to eat it.

This morning I spent a lot of time on my toilet and missed the ла train to the university.  My mother told me that I spent more ла time than a woman on my toilet.  I felt a mixed emotion of shame ла and anger.

When I was caught by the police and was kept with a group of ла delinquents, which added to my fear of being shut up.  I was ла afraid of the people near me and the future consequences.

Having suffered a not very pretty sight, I reacted by uttering ла some very cruel and sharp words.
When I came across an old friend whom I had not seen for a very ла long time.

A close friend died.
I saw some images of a decapitation in a horror film.

column41: A certain person started to say dreadful things very calmly, I ла felt hurt and disgusted.

When my relatives and I were in a car going slowly on a frozen ла road.

When I talk to my friends.
When I am walking on the streets and see a gang of thugs.
When people harrass me I feel oppressed by their behavior.
When I am with a friend and we have to leave each other.
When I saw a film in which the man suffered from an illness and    ла his skin came peeling off.
When I was in the toilet and someone came in.
[ When I act thinking that I know everything and I then realize ла that there were things I had not thought about, thus hurting ла others.]
[ Any situation in everyday life has this emotional sense, in ла class, in the street, at home, at the table..........]

The physical appearance of a meal.
I was with a group of people and everybody told me to do or say ла something.  It was a confusing, strong and traumatic situation ла for me.

One night, at a friend's place I realized that I had everything I ла most wished, around me.

When I saw parents punishing their little child for something he ла had not done.  In my opinion, even if he had done it he should ла not have been punished for it.
A friend of mine was hurt as he thought that our relationship was ла not the same as before and something had gone wrong.
When I was young, one day in the car we fell sick and ended up ла vomitting on each other.
The parents of a friend of mine surprised us and another couple ла sleeping in thier place.
A friend of mine felt bad because of something I had done to ла something that belonged to him.
When they told me that I had been admitted to the faculty of ла medicine.
Almost always when I go to fetch the results of an exam.
[ No description.]
When I decided not to out any longer with a girl whom I liked ла quite a lot.  This made me feel low for a some time.
I saw a program on T.V where they had to saw a skull for an        ла operation.
I was watching T.V with my parents and some pornographic scenes ла came on, I felt uncomfortable and tried to distract my parents ла attention by talking to them.
When I used an adjective for a person without knowing what it ла meant.   When I got to know the meaning, I felt guilty as it was ла a clear and unfair insult.
When I obtained good marks in a subject I had failed before.
When a friend of mine told me a horror story.
I was with my family and we found some abandoned puppies.  I ла wanted to help them but everyone said no.  We then left.
At my grandfather's death.
Seeing a film in which there were several bloody crimes.
At a concert an old man arrived and began to danse, sing and do ла silly things.
I had an argument with a friend of mine.  She would not let me ла speak and then I began to shout at her.  She got angry and left, ла I did not try to prevent her from leaving.
When I was told that they had got tickets for me for a film ла marathon I wanted to see.

I had applied for a job and they had assured me that the exams ла would take place a few months later.  A week later I went to ла obtain some more information and they told me that the exams had ла already taken place.
I received a letter from some friends, who do not live in Madrid, ла telling me that they would not come on holiday.  I had arranged ла everythiing for them.
I found a big, black spider near a bag of food.
I was in a very small class and the professor said something ла about me that made everyone look at me at the same time.
I had arranged to meet my friends at a certain place, and I was ла with other people.  My friends did not arrive and the people who ла were with me began to get tired.  My friends were one hour late.
The man I am going around with gave me a very special present.
I thought that I would be scolded for a comment I had made, which ла I should not have made.
My sister came back home and reproached me for not having tidied ла up the house, although I had been working all morning and she had ла done nothing.
At my grandfather's funeral.  I remembered that the thing he ла liked and respected most was earth, I thought that he had ла attained what he wanted and was not separated from it any longer.
I had to wash my grandmother because she did not get to the ла bathroom on time.
In a very crowded shop I was distracted and missed my turn in the ла queue.  A woman who was behind me began to shout at me asking me ла either to pay more attention or to leave.
When I was very young, one day, I kicked my grandmother and ла caused her an injury which took a long time to heal.
When I saw a friend of mine, whom I had not seen for a long time ла and I had lost his address and telephone number.
I was in my village when a bull jumped over a fence and started ла chasing my friends and me.  We were very frightened till we ла climbed up a tree.
When I saw a car run over a child, out of carelessness.
I failed a subject despite the fact that I had studied quite a ла lot for it.
When I was walking in a field which had a lot of manure.
I liked a boy and I would feel shy and then blush.  The more I ла wanted to avoid it the more I blushed.
I am not very affectionate and I feel guilty as I do not give as ла much affection as I receive.

I was spending the week-end with some friends.  We were waiting ла for another friend and we went to the meet him at the bus stop, a  ла woman we met there told us that the coach had already left.  I ла was afraid that I would not see my friend, but at last we found ла him.

I was walking down a little village at night.  There was nobody ла in the steet.  A dog began to bark, I felt that it was following ла me.  Then I began to run, the other dogs started barking too.  At ла last I arrived home.
My parents did not let me go on holidays with my friends.
I was told that a friend of mine was going to Mexico for good.
Finding a hair in the soup.

I was at the University dining room, alone, and at a table next ла to mine thre were several professors.  One of them asked me to ла join them.  I refused but she insisted.  All the others started ла looking at me and I had to move to their table.
I had promised to say goodbye to a person who was going on a ла trip, and I did not turn up.
I was on holidays, and I was going to meet a friend whom I had ла not seen for six months.  Again I felt very happy.
We were camping in the mountains, and a friend and I went for a ла walk.  It was getting darker and darker and we were not sure of ла the right way back.
I sent a book to a friend of mine.  The book meant a lot to me ла and he lost it.
To say goodbye to dear friends after the holidays.
Ever since I have been a child, the sight of any kind of wound.
At the seaside, when a wave suddenly came and took off my bikini.

One night, I went out with some friends for dinner and I did not ла tell my parents that I would come back late.  I thought of ла phoning but in the end I did not.  When I arrived home, my ла parents were very worried.
My sister in law was about to have a child, and there were some ла problems.  They had to do a Caesarean.  After a while, everything  ла was all right.
Waiting for my marks in a difficult subject.
I gave some personal information to a friend of mine, and he told ла it to some others who were implicated in the affair.
The holidays come to an end, and the next day we had to go back ла to University and to the exams.
There was a cat on the street.  It had been run over and its head was ла open.  We passed beside it.
At a meeting with over one hundred people, they decided who had to speak ла from the stand by drawing lots.
I had a small argument with a relative and some other people got ла implicated.  It resulted in a proper row.
Last course, when I passed with good marks three subjects which I had ла previously failed.
I was attacked by a man at a bus stop at night.
My mother told me that I could not go to the mountains.  Despite ла my age, as long as I am in her house I must do what she says.
When my nephew was taken to hospital with meningitis and we did ла not know what would happen.
I was drinking coffee in a cafe and I found a piece of scrubber ла in my cup.
When I went to my boyfriend's house for lunch and saw his ла parents, I felt that they were watching me all the time.
At school, I did not tell the teacher that it was me who ла had laughed, and she punished the entire class by making them ла stay behind for one hour.
One evening, I was with a group of friends having a talk.  There ла was a very trustful and joyful atmosphere.
We were walking in the park at night.  It was very dark and very ла late.  We began to hear foot steps all around us, and we could ла not find our way out.
[ One day I arrived home rather tired and found the house..... In ла addition I was asked many questions which I did not want to ла answer.]
I was selected to do a rest for a foreign ballet but I did not ла have the money to do it.
In a film there was a scene in which a rat was sliding on a bed, ла leaving a trace of blood behind, finally it entered the mouth of ла one of the actors.
I was swimming in the river and I lost the top of my bikini.  I ла did not notice it and came out of water.  There was a ла disagreeable classmate watching the scene.
At a party, several comments were made about the personal ла situation of one of the people present.  She was rather affected ла and uncomfortable.
It was Saturday, my duties were over for a few hours and I could ла at last be with the people I wanted to see.
One night, I was alone at home.  My fear was caused by some ла strange noises which put my imagination to work.
When I got to know about the reaction of a friend of mine in a ла certain situation.  I had not expected him to react that way.
I felt alone among a large number of people.  I was sad to see ла that nobody cared about what was happening to me.
I saw a sort of black worm being attacked by many ants.
When I met a friend of mine after several months.
When I noticed the negative changes in a friend's behaviour.
I was going to my village, after having been rather oppressed in ла Madrid.
I was watching a procession during the Holy week, and a penitent ла approached me.
My mother read a letter that a friend of mine had written to me ла telling me how she had got drunk the last time.
[ No response.]
I found a cockroach crushed between two folders in my bedroom, I ла called my mother.
I ride my motorbike in my village and everyone stares at me as if ла I was a rare specimen.
I was spending a few days at my aunt's place.  One night I got ла home very late, I had told them I was going to a party but I went ла to another place.  They were very worried.
Last Summer I achieved someting that I had been wanting for a ла long time.
I was in a camp and went out for a walk at night on my own.  I lost  ла my way and spent several hours looking for the camp.
My parents scolded me a lot for something I had not done.  It was ла my sister who had done it.
[ No response.]
At the hypocrisy of some of my friends.
I greeted and embraced the wrong person thinking that it was my ла friend.
Due to a misunderstanding on my part, two of my best friends ла quarelled.
When my brother was born, everything went all right.  It had been ла very likely that he would have a deficiency (my sister suffers ла from Down's Syndrome) and that my mother would be in danger.
When we got lost in Florence and the coach did not turn up until ла midnight.  I had no place to go to and there were strange reports ла at the police station.
When an English teacher unfairly made me repeat a semester which ла I thought I had passed.  I had to ask my parents for some more ла money to carry on studying.
The person whom I liked most left me for a friend of mine, after ла several months of mutual help and a profound knowledge of each ла other.
In a park near our home, a group of young people who were ла strangely dressed were seated in the middle of the street.  They ла began to eat while carressing each other.
I feel this emotion very often when I try to express my feelings ла in public, because other people do not understand my reactions ла and think that I am silly.
A friend of mine said in a group that she felt lonely and ла withdrawn from everyone because of mental deficiency.
When I passed the university entrance exam.  I had thus finished ла with a difficult period of my life and I was about to begin one ла which I had desired a lot.
When I was at home alone, I felt a super-natural force, dangerous ла for me and the people close to me.
When my father made my mother go through really terrible ла situations, I felt furious, impotent, nervous, upset, ........
When a person whom I loved and admired a lot died.  I felt empty, ла lonely, helpless, without support, not knowing what to do.
When I came to know that my father and his parents were : self ла interested, dirty, negative, egoist, bad peolpe,......
I think that the only time I really felt shame was when I was ла very young and I had to defecate on the street.  I was very ла worried in case someone should see me.
When I was young I felt guilty because I thought that I had ла commited a grave sin.
On my birthday, when I was given my presents.
We were riding in a friend's car.  He was driving very fast and ла suddenly a another car crossed the road in front of us.  My ла friend had to turn the car rapidly.
When I found one of my new pullovers wrinkled inside the ла wardrobe.  My brother had done it.
When I went to see the result of an exam and saw that I had ла failed.
When I was getting up, I found a live cockroach in my bedroom.
The mother of a friend of mine passed by me and saw me sitting ла on a boy's lap.  I tried to greet her but could not help ла blushing.
A friend of mine had the sleeves of a leather coat stolen from ла his car.  It was me who had left them there for everyone to see.

The final marks were to be given in the morning.  I wanted to get ла there late because I was very afraid.  When I arrived there, ла everybody was very happy and I had also passed.  We had a ла wonderful time all day long.
I went to visit a friend in hospital.  He was going to be ла operated the next day.  I was afraid that they would not let me ла in and I did not know what his reaction would be on seeing me.
A friend of mine played a joke on another friend over the ла telephone.  This friend, crying, called me and I got very angry ла and made the other person apologize.

A friend of mine told me that my boyfriend had been with another ла girl this Summer.  We had been going out together for four years ла and we had not done so for the last three months.  I could not ла believe it.
I was at a friend's place for lunch and she fell ill and ла vomited.
I was dancing in a theatre.  I was not sure whether some frieends ла of mine had come to see me.  I was very scared of doing things ла wrong.
Classes were over and I wanted to go home.  A friend of mine ла asked me to wait for half an hour to take him back home.  I said ла no.
On holiday, seeing the lanscape in Gerona.

They wanted me to pay for a ticket twice because they said that ла the one I had was out of date.
When I came back from my holidays.
When I saw an insect going up my arm.
When I entered a bar looking for a friend.
Arguing with my younger cousin.  She is rather a nuisance but I ла felt sorry.
When some friends of mine asked me to go camping with them for a ла fortnight.
Once, when I was very young, my mother left me alone in the ла house and came back very late.

When a person I did not know hurt a friend of mine.

Once, when I arrived home very late, my parents had an argument ла because of this; my mother wanted to stand up for me.
I phoned a friend of mine to ask her for news about the marks in ла an exam.  She told me that I had passed.

I was spending my summer holidays in a village.  My friend and I ла were coming back from a discotheque at night and we heard a noise ла from an alley.  We were very scared and we got into my friend's house. ла  A moment later, an unknown car picked up a person from this ла alley.
My mother and I had an argument over buying some clothes for me.  ла She did not accept the fact that I did not like the same things ла as her, and we ended up shouting at each other.
One day, I was home and there was a phone call informing me that ла some of my relatives had died in an accident.
When I saw a film in which there was a scene where women were cut ла to pieces.  Above all, it was the blood and the confusion which ла impressed me most.

A friend of mine trusted me to back her in a decision she had ла made.  But when the moment came I did not agree with her opinion.

When my brother hit his head and lost consciousness at the sports ла practice.  For some time he could not remember what had happened ла but he recovered later.
I get angry with my brothers and sisters when they do something ла that I do not like.  They know this and still do it so as to ла tease me.
When my grandfather died.
When opened a box of biscuits and found worms inside.
When I was young I was told to to the shop to buy a dozen eggs.  ла I went and asked for one egg and the people in the shop laughed ла at me and so did my family when I told them what had happened.
When I arrived home late at night.  I know that my mother gets ла worried and this made me feel angry.
When I spoke to my daughter and wished her luck for the ла examinations she was about to take.

When I was told that my uncle had passed away.
The transport to pick us up for lunch was always late and the ла driver made the same excuse every day.
One day when I came back home, I found my favourite dish broken.  ла I blamed the servant for it, later I found out that it was not ла the servant but my daughter who had broken it.
When I did not give back a text book to a friend in time.
When a cousin of mine was discharged from the hospital after       ла a long illness.  I had thought that this illness would never end.
When a man who had a knife grabbed me and threatened me with it,   ла during my holidays in Monze.ла
A certain friend tried to push me off a seat in a very violent ла way for no apparent reason.  It may be that he was excited about ла something.
When the neighbour of a friend of mine was stabbed to death by ла thieves in Kabwe.  They stole his van.
When we were young, a friend of mine tried to dissect a frog while  ла we were playing near his home.
The time I shouted at most of my friends at a party.  It was as if ла  all my friends had done something wrong, or may be it was the ла influence of the beer.

When I was about six years old, I mistook a cat for a leopard      ла when it entered my room at night.

column41: When I lost my father on the 25th of September,1970.  He died of ла a sore on the leg.

When someone whom I trusted, disappointed me terribly.

When I was victimized for running away with a girl who was ла somebody else's wife and niece at the same time.  I was very ла angry over this issue because I was told to pay him money after ла having been punished for it.
1976, Soweto uprising in South Africa and the racist Gout's ла reaction to the students demands concerning the educational ла system.

The time I qualified to enter secondary school.

When I was mistakenly accused of being a thief when I accidently ла gave a fake coin at a counter.  I realized this before I handed ла over the coin, but the man called me a thief and called a ла witness.

column41: This is an event I will never forget.  I am considered a good ла mimic.  This particular day we were waiting for a professor ла to take her class. My classmate used her personal relations to get a seat for a ла subject that I wanted also.  I had taken the pains to help him ла apply and I did not get selected.  I did not like this as he had ла not told me the facts earlier, he need not have lied to me.

During a recent meeting, Mr. A showed his excitement and ла overindulged in the notes delivered.  Though his curiosity could ла not be blamed, his way of accquiring knowledge was an extreme ла behaviour e.g he always tried to know what I was reading and ла gained everything he could.
When I was doing my homework at home, some relatives came and ла advised me to help my mother do the house-work.
While quarreling with my brother I broke the glass door of the ла cupboard and a china doll.  We were scolded by my father for ла breaking the door but we did not tell him about the door.

An inter-college basket-ball match.
Something was stolen.
When I learnt that my close friend was going to immigrate.

During a meeting.
Failed to keep an appointment.
When I told my girlfriend a joke openly and frankly.

The behaviour of people spitting everywhere.
I could not finish my homework on time.
After masturbation.

Someone played a trick on me.
When the thing that made my friends and relatives sad happened to ла them.
It was a narrow and dirty passage which was located near the ла market and I had to stand there to wait for people.
I had something wrong, saying wrong things and being impolite to ла someone, and this had embarrassed the this person.  And I ла still meet the person.
I said something which was against my conscience.
Several good friends made me a surprise visit and this made me ла happy.  They are my closest friends and we had not seen each ла other for a long time.
The hero was chased by a terrible vampire in a suspense and ла horror film shown on T.V.

I worked with several classmates on a project.  I was very ла anxious about the project while my partners showed no concern  ла and when we had meetings on the project my classmates  did not ла pay any attention.  Some of them read books while the others ла argued on irrelevant questions.  The meeting would go on for two ла hours without the main theme being discussed.  We wasted time and ла could not reach a compromise.  My classmates avoided doing the ла work and the responsibilities, they seemed to value other ла projects more than this one.
One of my good friends had to migrate to America.  Our friendship ла had developed quite well and it was a pity as our friendship would ла fade.

In a study group, a person always liked to argue on some ла unimportant, irrelevant and minor points.  He tried to persuade    ла others in an unfriendly way.  He was obstinate and would not accept  ла other's point of view.

Once my presentation was the worst among my classmates as I had ла not prepared it well and had not seen it as important.  My ла presentation was so confused that it clearly showed my poor ла preparation.

I joked with an unfamiliar friend in an obstinate tone.  I was ла afraid of his misunderstanding me and being hurt and angry at me. ла  I felt sorry over my conduct and thought that I had to find an ла opportunity to apologize.

I remember my religious experience.  During  a gospel camp, a few ла friends of mine decided to believe in God.  The joy that I felt ла at that time was more than words can express.  I blessed them and ла praised God in my heart.

My friend and I had offended our classmate unintenionally.  We ла wanted to apologize to her so we decided to visit her.  We knew that she ла was stubborn so we were frightened.  When we rang her door bell, ла our fear was at it's climax
My girlfriend disliked it when I played majong (a game of gambling).  ла I expressed my regrets and when I went to see her she neglected my ла existance.  I was very angry and left in displeasure.
When I said good-bye to my girlfriend.  I had spent two years on ла developing this relationship and it was unsuccessful, I felt very ла sad.

column41: Once in primary five, I had forgotten to take a book to class and ла the teacher punished me by asking me to stand at the back of the ла class.  I thought about the way my mother would react if she saw ла me being punished.  My mother was very good to me and though she ла did not see me punished, I felt sorry for her.

I had fixed a meeting with my classmates and I missed it as I was ла tired.  Besides everyone at the meeting was a stranger to me and ла I did not want to make friends with them.  Whatever the reasons - I  ла felt guilty.

I learnt from the newspaper that I had been accepted at the ла Chinese university of H.K.  It was 7 o'clock in the morning.  ла Later I told my family and relatives about it and had tea with ла them very joyfully.

column41: During a football match, the other team was rude and they hurt my ла team members and me.  The coach was prejudiced against us and ла punished us unreasonably.  Later we fought with each other and ла the match had to be cut short.

A  group of youngsters dressed in fads talked foul language on a ла bus.  They also insulted the  pedestrians on the road and were ла impolite to the passengers of the bus.

In a Christian gathering's lucky draw I mistook a girl's name for ла mine (a boy's name).  I realized my mistake only when I went up ла to the stage for the prize.  I did not know what to do as ла everyone was looking at me.  I blushed and went back to my seat.

While playing basketball I broke a team member's spectacles.  His ла face was injured by the  pieces of glass.  It was not serious but ла I felt guilty and blamed myself for being too careless and ла vigorous in my game.
After a busy day I went back to my hostel.  I closed the door and ла had a drink, then I read my favourite book on the bed.  Suddenly ла I felt peace and joy.

When I went home and there was nobody, I waited till 2 A.M and      ла still nobody.  I was suddenly scared and anxious as this had never ла happened before.  In addition my mother was very weak and I ла feared that she had met with an accident.  Therefore I was anxious  ла all night.

Yesterday I read in the newspaper that a 30 year old woman had ла abused her 2 month old son and had caused his death.  I was very ла angry after reading this as this is not a human act and to abuse ла so fragile a life is not a forgivable sin.

I had a schoolmate who went to the hospital as her brain was ла bleeding.  She fell unconscious for three days and when I went ла to see her I saw the miserable state the family was in.  Moreover ла I could not do nothing for her.  I was very sad.  Finally, she ла died.
A tiresome person held me up all day long.  I was very busy then ла (I can not remember what the problem was).  He continously tried ла to make me talk to him and disturbed me.

"|1|;;

column41: After an exam I was in a very bad mood as I had done it very       ла badly.  At home, my mother took so long to ask me how things had  ла gone that I lost my temper.  I overreacted and made my mother cry. ла She still prepared lunch for me and did not scold me .  Suddenly, ла I thought that it was my fault and I started crying.  ла
I was appreciated by others, especially my family members and my ла friends.

Whenever I am alone in a dark room, walk alone on the street, ла sleep alone in the room at night or see something which is only ла partly visible.  This emotion was very strong when as an 8 year   ла old child I saw something horrible.

[ Whenever I put myself in other's shoes and try to make the ла person happy, comfort him or make friends and I am misunderstood ла and rejected, especially when this person is a family member or a friend.]

There was a conflict of interest between me and a close friend of ла mine.  He only thought about his own interest and not about our ла friendship.  This behaviour hurt his friends.  Another incident ла is when a friend isolated himself without giving any reasons.
When I saw a lot of rubbish and animal waste on the floor.

When I was emotionally unstable I said things which may have hurt ла others or made them feel unhappy.  When I calmed down I realized ла that I had been selfish and had not taken into consideration the ла feelings of others.  Then I felt ashamed as someone pointed out my ла behaviour to me.

[ When I break someone's things out of carelessness, or do something  ла to make others feel unhappy  or hurt the self-esteem / self-confidence  ла of others, especially if they happen to be friends or family members.]
When I received the letter informing that I had been accepted to ла be a Chinese university student, I was excited as I had longed ла for it.

One day when I was a little boy, my friends asked me to play ла with them outside and to catch some boys.  However our parents ла did not know that we were out and when I got home it was very ла late and I feared being scolded by my parents.
When I learnt that a friend of mine had talked about me to ла another friend and had said wrong things about my abilities and ла attitudes.  I was very angry.

About two years ago my girlfriend suggested that we separate.  ла This really gave me a shock as I had never thought that she would ла say such things.  The reason she gave me was that we were not ла suited for each other.
Once while studying for my exam I found so many complicated words ла that it disgusted me.
When I was young I felt ashamed when our relatives visited us and ла I hid myself.
I was so excited once that I told my classmate that she was old, ла this hurt her and I felt guilty.
[ During a certain period, I felt successful and extremely satisfied.   ла When I found that any tasks or decisions that I had made were better  ла than expected.]
I am scared when I stroll alone on the Chung Chi college campus.

One day, I discussed a very important question with A.  A ла suddenly declared that he would not accept my position and ла thought that he himself was right.  Moreover, he attacked  ла strongly, not my opinion but me personally.
When I learnt that I had failed an exam,  This not only influenced ла my emotions but also other important tasks, it also made my ла record imperfect.
[ I would classify subjectively, a certain gesture or the way of ла talking of a person as disgusting or inacceptable.]
One day I felt dizzy during a lecture.  When the lecturer asked ла us as to who had heard the fairy tale - I was the only one who ла put up his hand and this surprised the whole class.

We always made a lot of noise during a certain lecture.  This may ла have been because we did not respect the lecturer. Finaly, the ла lecturer could not tolerate it and he scolded us angrily and ла pointed out our misbehaviour.
I felt happy when I received the letter telling me that I had ла been admitted to the university.

During the first year in university I had bad results in both ла the terms, especially the first term.  I was afraid that  I would ла not be promoted to the next year and that the others would go ла ahead of me.
Once my father slapped my mother for a small quarrel.

A few years ago my mother suffered from canccer and died within ла two years.  We had not finished our studies then and could not ла bear our responsibilities as her children.  My mother had tried ла her best to take care of us but she lived in pain these two ла years.  Neither the doctor nor we could do anything for her as ла cancer is incurable.  I was very eager to replace her in ла suffernig , even die instead of her.

I used to play with a group of classmates and I found out later ла that they were cheap in thought, behaviour and conduct - they ла would smoke, fight and speak foul language.  I thought that they ла destroyed the image of college students.
It was discovered that I had received a warning letter as my ла G.P.A was very low.

Many years back I quarrelled with my younger brother for a small ла reason.  I used a pole to beat him and nearly broke his arm.  He ла recovered after a treatment which lasted several months.  After ла this our relationship was worse and he would not listen to me.

One Saturday afternoon, I deliberately dressed up nicely (I had ла been in a bad mood of late).  I hoped to go for a walk in the ла soft sunlight to try and uplift my spirits.  When I was having ла lunch in the canteen, two of my male classmates asked me as to ла why I was dressed so nicely (they had seldom joked with me ла before).  One of them said that he had a lounge suit and we would ла look very nice if we wore them together.

The exam was drawing near and I wanted to prepare for it.  But I ла had a lot of other things to do so I did not have much time to prepare  ла for the exams.  Whenever I sat down to study I was scared that I would  ла not be able to finish it.

A female classmate was always late for meetings which were for ла the homework and not social gatherings.  We were very busy and ла the deadline was close but we had to waste half an hour or an ла hour waiting for her as we could do nothing else then.

After a meeting ended we started talking about when we would ла have the next discussion ( I had many tests the coming week and ла could not have a meeting in between, I thought that they would ла understand this as they had always done).  They did not ла understand my problem and thought that I should not have so many ла other activities.  Their reaction made me burst into tears.
When I was studying in the library a pair of lovers were sitting ла next to me talking in an intense and soft voice.  They were ла disturbing others.

During an informal discussion I contributed a lot even though I ла had not spent much time studying.  Whenever someone said that ла someone was not paying attention, or that he had too many other ла things to do, or that the persoon was not trying his best, I ла would feel ashamed.

Our class had organized a picnic in November.  I was the class ла representative so I became the organizor.  However the picnic ла was postponed by one week and I had something else to do then. ла Initially I did not ponder on what to do and decided to go for ла the picnic.  When I had the time to think about it I thought that ла my decision was wrong.  My classmates thought that I would go as ла I had signed my name but I did not go.  I told another class ла representative that I was not going but he did not know the ла reason behind my not going.  After the picnic my classmates asked ла me why I had not gone to the picnic and everytime someone ла mentioned it I was apologetic.  I should have decided right in ла the begining that I would not go and then they would not see me ла as irresponsible i.e promising to go and changing my mind ла afterwards.

It was the first time I met him (my boyfriend Mr.W).  It was ла during the first term Summer vacations.  We met each other while ла handing in our homework.  He invited me have a trip with him and ла we were together till 8 P.M.

The day the results of the certificate exam came out.  I went to ла school and at first I did not feel frightened.  By the time I ла reached the fourth floor ( the results were being given on the ла fifth floor) I found it difficult to walk and felt that I would ла die.

One day I had sunned my favourite shirt and was putting it back ла in the wardrobe when my younger brother snatched it from me and ла wore it.  He had not had a bath and was very dirty.  I scolded him ла but he answered back and locked himself up in a room.  I was very ла angry so I starteed kicking on the door and abusing him loudly ла and freely.

When I was a child I was playing on the upper deck of the bed ла with my brother.  My parents slept on the lower deck.  My father ла felt disgusted and beat me up.  I felt very sad as my father had ла never beaten me or scolded me before.

My boyfriend and I did not have any contact with each other during  ла the Summer holidays.  I met him the day of the registration and looked  ла through him.  In the canteen he asked me if I wanted to have a drink and  ла I said no as I did not want him to do me a favour.

On Christmas eve I went to a classmate's home with other ла classmates.  The next morning when I came out of the toilet she ла said something and I did not understand what she was saying.  ла When she pointed at my trousers I discovered that I had forgotten ла to zip them up.  I rushed back to the toilet but by the time the ла others had guessed what had happened.

One night,when I was in primary 5 or 6, I felt thirsty so I ла fetched the thermos to pour a cup of water for myself.  Then I ла saw my brother lowering his head and I, jokingly, poured the       ла water on his head.
I had gone camping with my old classmates and there was a storm.  ла We were in a flurry but at that time I felt the love and concern ла of my friends.

I was on a trip to Phillipines during Summer and I was staying in ла a hotel.  The room I was staying in was very silent and had very ла dim lights.  The last night I felt frightened and lay awake - I ла could hear some sounds around me and dared not open my eyes - I ла waited for dawn.

I had a very good friend in secondary school.  The year after our ла graduation I prepared to celebrate her birthday and I called off ла all my appointments.  I got together the other friends and we ла were ready to give the entire day to her.  However this friend ла disappeared on her birthday.  When I phoned another friend I ла didcovered thay she was busy, I did not call her anymore.
I am a Christian but I cannot find any meaning in life . It ла seems that I am deceiving myself but I cannot find the way out.

A brother from one of the Christian fellowship often phoned me ла and talked to me for half an hour or more.  However there was ла nothing important in the conversation and I found the person very ла disgusting.
I felt shame when I found that I was almost last in the exam.

Once I bought my sister a pair of sports shoes as she was going ла to join an athletic meet.  However the shoes were a little big ла and had a few flaws.  She muttered all the way and blamed me for ла having wasted her money anf I felt guilty.
When the result of the certificate exam was announced.  I was ла surprised and happy as the result was better than I had ла expected.
When I was young I got lost on the street and the police found me ла after a day.

My sister once stole my mother's money and made her very angry.  ла After this my mother would beat her up for unreasonable reasons.  ла One day my sister lent her book to a friend without telling my ла mother about it.  When my mother learnt this she beat her up and ла even threatened her with a pair of scissors.
My academic result was poor and I had to repeat the second year.  ла I felt sad about the coming several years.
My mother was always fastidious about my room, bed time, etc.  ла She treated us strictly and punished us physically.   These ла things were intolerable.
I misunderstood a girl and thought that she loved me.  One day ла when I was talking to her, her boyfriend appeared and I felt ла ashamed.
When I was in P3 I was always punished as I would forget to do my ла homework.  The first time that I was punished and not allowed to ла leave school, I slipped out of school.
I was admited to the Chinese university of Hong Kong.  The day ла the results were announced I looked in the newspaper and saw my ла candidature number.

One year, when I went to a camp, I was chased by a dog.  I tried ла hard and finally managed to escape from it.  My torch suddenly ла went off and we talked about ghost stories and I thought that ла there were ghosts.
When I was in F4 I played a basket-ball match against another ла school's team.  One of their team members kicked a team-mate of ла mine so I kicked him back and we had a fight with each other.
I received the mid-term exam paper of one of my major subjects ла and I found that I had failed it.
Once at a camp a classmate criticized me in front of others.  Now ла I find that this classmate is very disgusting.

When I was in F4 I led my class to a riot.  However the form ла master said that my conduct was good and asked me to tell him the ла names of those who had taken part in it.   I replied that I did ла not know.
I promised to join a meeting but did not turn up as I did not ла want to do the work.
[ When my performance (homework or other work) is better than others.]
I found a problem in homework which would not get solved although ла I tried my best.

I had a date with my girlfriend, the time and place had not been ла fixed.  I asked her to phone me an hour later as it was midnight ла and I did not want to disturb her family.  I waited several hours ла for her call, she did not call me that night.
When I found that my ability to do ordinary work was worse than ла my fellow mates.
I made friends with a classmate whose behaviour I did not like - ла he tried to flatter other people and did not respect me.
My guilty behaviour was found out by others.
When my behaviour was immoral - thinking about sex.

During my Summer vacations I planned a carnival for the community ла youth center with a few other volunteers.  I was the head of the ла organizors and we spent over a month planning it.  During this ла period we got to know and understood each other.  We ла discovered each others potential and we planned many interesting ла things for the carnival.  The day of the carnival everything was ла bright, the programmes went well and the attendants enjoyed it.  ла I felt extremely excited about it.
[ No response.]

I was a prefect at secondary school.  On the sports day I told ла others that I would take down the names of the people who ла misbehaved and after some time I sat down for a brief rest.  ла Suddenly the head prefect came and scolded me in front of others. ла  I was very angry as there were other prefects sitting and he ла picked on me.  I thought that a brief rest was not  serious ла enough to be blamed.
[ No response.]

I had joined a youth group that observed the affairs of our ла community and so I had many opportunities to contact the ла government and the committee members of the district board (a ла local executive structure).  We always tried to consult and ла discuss with them, but we found that such people did not ла understand community affairs and they even dampened our ла enthusiasm in local affairs.  I did not understand why they had ла decided to work as community leaders.

One day I was the leader of the weekly meeting of the Church ла fellowship.  That day I had been preparing for the exams and did ла not estimate the time to travel to the church right and I was ла twenty minutes late.  As I had not prepared well I led the ла meeting badly.  I was ashamed of myself.

I borrowed my classmate's notebook one week before the ла examination and I promised to give it back to her in two days ла time.  I was very busy at that time and forgot many things; as I ла was not very often at home she could not contact me.  When I ла started my revision I realized that her notebook had been on my ла desk for five days.  I contacted her immediately and gave it back ла to her.  Though she did not say anything I felt very guilty.
When high level results were declared, I found my candidature ла number.  I was very happy as I had not expected it.  As I had been  ла injured before the examination and I had performed poorly.
Once, when I was ten, I could not remember why my mother was so ла angry.  She fainted suddenly and I was very scared as I did not ла know what to do .

When I got into a bus I found that my wallet had been stolen. ла It was not a great loss from the monetary point of view but I ла lost some documents - identity papers.  As a result I had to ла spend several days in order to get a new one.  I will always ла remember all the work I had to do and the bad treatment I ла suffered because of the bureaucratic behaviour of the civil ла servant.  I had already had bad luck and they treated me like a ла criminal.   At one point of time I really wanted to quarrel with ла them.

I quarrelled with my younger sister because I had said something ла against her boyfriend.  Consequently she looked through me when ла she saw me as she thought that I was trying to separate them.  ла She had misunderstood me.
A few days back, I walked on a heap of faeces while walking on ла the road.  I got goose flesh because of this.
During the English lesson we were required to do a play.  A few ла days after doing it the teacher asked us to do it again at a meeting  ла and I forgot my part.

Once, my friend and I went to the Tai 60 to cycle.  My mother had ла told me not to go.  Unfortunately I broke my pectoral girdle and ла had to go to hospital.  When my mother  came to see me I felt ла guilty as I had not listened to her and I had to soon sit for a ла public examination.

They took us back into the hall and we talked freely.  We ла|were together for about an hour and during this time we felt ла|that they were very sincere."|1|;;

column41: At noon one Sunday I received a phone call telling me that my ла mother had been knocked down by a car at the street crossing and ла that her husband should go and see her.  I could not believe this ла as my father and my mother had gone out together to buy lunch ла boxes.  However I immediately ran to the scene of the accident.

The day the results of the Chinese university was announced I ла should have been very happy; however my grandmother, because of  ла her prejudice and misunderstanding, started a  quarrel with my ла mother.  She expected me to take her side and she deliberately ла talked of my mother's wrong doings.  I was very angry because - ла one my grandmother was not being reasonable and two because it ла should have been a happy day and three we had moved into a new ла house that day.

When I was in lower six class during the Summer I joined a ла research group of the Chinese university student union.  I knew ла a lot of CV students there.  A year later one of them was ла travelling in mainland China and he got T.B.  He died a few weeks ла after coming back to H.K.  We all got together for the funeral ла and when I looked at the body for the last time I felt extremely ла sad.

During these Summer vacations a schoolmate who was not in my ла class went to Britain.  Before he left, his classmates and some ла of us who were accquainted with him had a B.B.Q on the beach.  ла When I arrived I saw that some people , who were not close ла friends of the departing person(person A), were playing mahjong.  ла Some others were playing bridge and A had nothing to do, besides ла it was A who had prepared the food.  Later when we wanted to talk ла and his classmates did not even have the decency to listen to him.  ла They only asked him a few questions half-heartedly and then they ла talked on their own.  Some of their conversation was against me and  ла another classmate.

When I was in lower six I joined an interview group to ла interview the general public.  One of my friends in the group ла lost her purse and she was very nervous.  Five of us had to go ла another place so we left her, and planned to see her later.  Then ла I heard her describing how her purse looked.  I realized that I ла had seen her purse on the floor and had not wanted to do any ла thing about it.

I went to a friend's baptism as she became a Christian after me ла and I realized that she was more enthusiastic about her spiritual ла life than I was.  When I was with my brothers and sisters of ла Christ I had a guilty feeling which could not be dismissed ла easily.  When pepole asked me as to when I would be baptised my ла guilt feeling deepened.

When I received the result slip of the higher level examination ла (an university entrance exam) and saw that I had a very good ла possibility of being accepted into the university, I felt very ла excited.
One camping night, I listened to the ghost stories told by my ла classmates.
Last week I had planned to play tennis and had booked a tennis ла court.   However when I arrived at the university gym the clerk ла told me that the court was being used for lessons.
